entry.title: Corrections to "Homotopy theory of nonsymmetric operads, I, II"
entry.summary: We correct a mistake in the construction of push-outs along free morphisms of algebras over a nonsymmetric operad in arXiv:1101.1634 [math.AT], and we fix the affected results in arXiv:1101.1634 [math.AT] and arXiv:1304.6641 [math.AT].

entry.title: A Convenient Category for The Homotopy Theory of Concurrency
entry.summary: Withdrawn paper because the results are published in math.AT/0308054 and math.AT/0308063.

entry.title: Chromatic redshift
entry.summary: Notes for the author's MSRI lecture in January 2014.

entry.title: Homotopy branching space and weak dihomotopy
entry.summary: Withdrawn paper because the results are recycled in several other papers and a new definition of T-homotopy is proposed in math.AT/0505152.

entry.title: Supplement 2 to the paper "Floating bundles and their applications"
entry.summary: This paper is the supplement to the section 2 of the paper "Floating bundles and their applications" (math.AT/0102054). Below we study some properties of category, connected with cobordism rings of FBSP. In particular, we shall show that it is the tensor category.

entry.title: The Auslander-Reiten quiver of a Poincare duality space
entry.summary: In a previous paper, math.AT/0304079, Auslander-Reiten triangles and quivers were introduced into algebraic topology. This paper shows that over a Poincare duality space, each component of the Auslander-Reiten quiver is isomorphic to ZA_{\infty}.

entry.title: Closed symmetric monoidal structure and flow
entry.summary: The category of flows is not cartesian closed. We construct a closed symmetric monoidal structure which has moreover a satisfactory behavior from the computer scientific viewpoint.
entry.arxiv:comment: 14 pages ; Third paper corresponding to the content of math.AT/0201252

entry.title: Addendum to "Coarse homology theories"
entry.summary: This article corrects two mistakes in the article "Coarse homology theories" [math.AT/0106183].
entry.arxiv:comment: Published by Algebraic and Geometric Topology at http://www.maths.warwick.ac.uk/agt/AGTVol3/agt-3-38.abs.html

entry.title: The homotopy branching space of a flow
entry.summary: In this talk, I will explain the importance of the homotopy branching space functor (and of the homotopy merging space functor) in dihomotopy theory. The paper is a detailed abstract of math.AT/0304112 and math.AT/0305169.
entry.arxiv:comment: Expository paper ; 11 pages ; to appear in GETCO'03 proceeding
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Electronic Notes in Theoretical Computer Science, vol. 100 : pp 95-109, 2004

entry.title: On the cohomology of SL(2,Z[1/p])
entry.summary: In this paper we compute the integral cohomology of the discrete groups SL(2,Z[1/p]), where p is any prime.

entry.title: On Combinatorial Descriptions of Homotopy Groups of $ΣK(π,1)$
entry.summary: We give a combinatorial description of homotopy groups of $\Sigma K(\pi,1)$. In particular, all of the homotopy groups of the $3$-sphere are combinatorially given.

entry.title: On Combinatorial Calculations for the James--Hopf maps
entry.summary: We give some formulas of the James-Hopf maps by using combinatorial methods. An application is to give a product decomposition of the spaces $\Omega\Sigma^2(X)$.

entry.title: A Product Decomposition of $Ω^3_0Σ${\bf R}$P^2$
entry.summary: We give a specific product decomposition of the base-point path connected component of the triple loop space of the suspension of the projective plane.

entry.title: Topological transformation groups
entry.summary: This paper surveys some results and methods in topological transformation groups.

entry.title: On some examples of group actions and group extensions
entry.summary: We study and relate certain actions and extensions involving 2-groups.

entry.title: Exponents and the cohomology of finite groups
entry.summary: Provides a counterexample to a long standing conjecture of A. Adem regarding the behaviour of the integral cohomology of a p-group.

entry.title: The KO-theory of Toric Manifolds
entry.summary: We use the Adams spectral sequence to compute the KO-theory of all toric manifolds and certain singular toric varieties.

entry.title: Extension dimension and C-spaces
entry.summary: Some generalizations of the classical Hurewicz formula are obtained for extension dimension and C-spaces.

entry.title: Equivariant Cohomology and Representations of the Symmetric Group
entry.summary: A cohomological study is made of an equivariant map betwen the configuration space of n points in space and the flag manifold of U(n).

entry.title: A remark on sl_2 approximation of the Kontsevich integral of the unknot
entry.summary: We give a formula for an sl_2 approximation of the Kontsevich integral of the unknot.

entry.title: Introduction to the language of stacks and gerbes
entry.summary: This is an introduction to gerbes for topologists, with emphasis on non-abelian cohomology.

entry.title: Constructing and Deconstructing Group Actions
entry.summary: We survey some results concerning finite group actions on products of spheres.
entry.arxiv:comment: Based on lecture at Northwestern University Algebraic Topology Conference, March 2002

entry.title: Errata to: Local contribution to the Lefschetz fixed point formula
entry.summary: This note contains a correction to the paper, ``Local contribution to the Lefschetz fixed point formula'', Inv. Math. 111 (1993), pp. 1-33.

entry.title: An Atiyah-Hirzebruch spectral sequence for KR-theory
entry.summary: We construct a spectral sequence for computing KR-theory, analogous to the spectral sequence relating motivic cohomology to algebraic K-theory.

entry.title: Multiplicative structures on homotopy spectral sequences II
entry.summary: The paper summarizes the construction of pairings on some standard spectral sequences in algebraic topology.

entry.title: HKR Theorem for Smooth S-algebras
entry.summary: We derive an \'etale descent formula for topological Hochschild homology and prove a HKR theorem for smooth S-algebras.

entry.title: Mod p homology of the stable mapping class group
entry.summary: We calculate the homology of the mapping class group in the stable range. The calculation is based on Madsen and Weiss' proof of the "Generalised Mumford Conjecture".

entry.title: On the perturbation lemma, and deformations
entry.summary: We have one more look at the (homological) perturbation lemma and we point out some non-standard consequences, including the relevance to deformations.

entry.title: A note on the Thom isomorphism in geometric (co)homology
entry.summary: Using geometric homology and cohomology we give a simple and conceptual proof of the Thom isomorphism theorem.

entry.title: On the cobar construction of a bialgebra
entry.summary: We show that the cobar construction of a DG-bialgebra is a homotopy G-algebra. This implies that the bar construction of this cobar is a DG-bialgebra as well.

entry.title: Notes on the Milnor conjectures
entry.summary: These are some notes on the two Milnor conjectures and their proofs (due to Voevodsky, Orlov-Vishik-Voevodsky, and Morel).

entry.title: Polynomials Maps and Even Dimensional Spheres
entry.summary: We construct, for every even dimensional sphere $S^n$, $n >1$, and every odd integer $k$, a homogeneous polynomial map $f: S^{n}\to S^{n}$ of Brouwer degree $k$ and algebraic degree $2|k|-1$.

entry.title: Cohomology of lambda-rings
entry.summary: A cohomology theory for lambda-rings is developed. This is then applied to study deformations of lambda-rings.

entry.title: On Sikora's spectral sequences
entry.summary: The Swan, Leray and Leray-Serre spectral sequences of a compact Hausdorff HLC space acted on by a discrete group are shown to be isomorphic.

entry.title: Quasi-categories vs Segal spaces
entry.summary: We show that complete Segal spaces and Segal categories are Quillen equivalent to quasi-categories.

entry.title: Novikov-Betti numbers and the fundamental group
entry.summary: We prove that nonvanishing of the first Novikov-Betti number implies that the fundamental group contains a nonabelian free subgroup.

entry.title: v1-periodic homotopy groups of the Dwyer-Wilkerson space
entry.summary: The Dwyer-Wilkerson space DI(4) is the only exotic 2-compact group. We compute its v1-periodic homotopy groups.

entry.title: A few remarks concerning complex-analytic metric spaces
entry.summary: The special case of closed subsets of C^n is briefly discussed.

entry.title: The cohomology of certain groups
entry.summary: Computations in the cohomology of finite groups.
entry.arxiv:comment: PhD thesis (Cambridge, 1990) with one extra chapter added 1992

entry.title: Lecture by Michael Hopkins: the string orientation of tmf
entry.summary: These are the notes of a lecture held by Michael Hopkins in march 2007, at the Talbot workshop.

entry.title: CW-groups associated with wrap groups
entry.summary: This article is devoted to the investigation of wrap groups of connected fiber bundles. CW-groups associated with wrap groups are studied.

entry.title: Cohomology $C_{\infty}$-algebra and Rational Homotopy Type
entry.summary: In the rational cohomology of a 1-connected space a structure of $C_{\infty}$-algebra is constructed and it is shown that this object determines the rational homotopy type

entry.title: The Torsion of Homology Groups of M(E,I)-sets
entry.summary: We consider the torsion of homology groups of right pointed sets over a partially commutative monoid M(E,I)

entry.title: Power operations for Morava E-theory of height 2 at the prime 2
entry.summary: Explicit calculations of the algebraic theory of power operations for a specific Morava E-theory spectrum are given, without detailed proofs.

entry.title: An integral Riemann-Roch theorem for surface bundles
entry.summary: This paper proves an integral version of the Riemann-Roch theorem for surface bundles, comparing the standard cohomology classes with the cohomology classes coming from the symplectic group.

entry.title: The Homology groups of right pointed sets over a partially commutative monoid
entry.summary: We study the homology of pointed sets over a partially commutative monoid.

entry.title: Formality of the chain operad of framed little disks
entry.summary: We extend Tamarkin's formality of the little disk operad to the framed little disk operad.

entry.title: Projective resolution of modules over the noncommutative algebra
entry.summary: We give an explicit algorithm to compute a projective resolution of a module over the noncommutative ring based on the noncommutative Groebner bases theory.

entry.title: On K(1)-local SU-bordism
entry.summary: This paper works towards a K(1)-local multiplicative splitting of SU-bordism.

entry.title: Topological aspects of the Dvoretzky Theorem
entry.summary: We explore possibilities and limitations of a purely topological approach to the Dvoretzky Theorem.

entry.title: Derived Algebraic Geometry VI: E_k Algebras
entry.summary: In this paper, we study algebras over the little cubes operads introduced by Boardman and Vogt, using the formalism of higher category theory.

entry.title: On the idempotency of some composite functors
entry.summary: In this note we present examples of localization functors (in the category of spaces) whose composition with certain cellularization functors is not idempotent, and vice versa.

entry.title: Correction: Stable homotopy classification of $BG_{p}^{\wedge}$
entry.summary: We correct the proof of the main theorem of our paper of the same title (Topology, 34, no.3, 633-649, 1995).

entry.title: Loop homology of quaternionic projective spaces
entry.summary: We determine the Batalin-Vilkovisky algebra structure of the integral loop homology of quaternionic projective spaces and octonionic projective plane.

entry.title: Tutorial on the braid groups
entry.summary: This is an introduction to the braid groups, as presented in the summer school and workshop on braid groups at the National University of Singapore in June 2007.

entry.title: A finite time blowup result for quadratic ODE's
entry.summary: This short paper is dedicated to Mauricio Peixoto who abstracted the practical theory of ODE's and to David Rand who applied the subsequent powerful abstract theory to practical problems.

entry.title: An explicit description of the simplicial group $K(A,n)$
entry.summary: We give a new explicit construction for the simplicial group $K(A,n)$. We explain the topological interpretation and discuss some possible applications.

entry.title: The Multiplication on BP
entry.summary: BP is an E_4 ring spectrum. The E_4 structure is unique up to automorphism.

entry.title: Mod 2 Morava K-theory for Frobenius complements of exponent dividing 2^n 9
entry.summary: We determine the cohomology rings K(s)*(BG) at 2 for all finite Frobenius complements G of exponent dividing 2n 9.

entry.title: A Homeomorphism Invariant of Polyhedra
entry.summary: In this paper, we define a new bigraded L-homology on finite simplicial complexes and prove that L-homology is a homeomorphism invariant of polyhedra.

entry.title: The nerve of a crossed module
entry.summary: We give an explicit description for the nerve of crossed module of categories.

entry.title: Tropicalisation for Topologists
entry.summary: This is an attempt to look at the tropical geometry from topological point of view.
entry.arxiv:comment: A set of notes on tropical sets (no claim of originality). Comments are welcome

entry.title: The fundamental group and covering spaces
entry.summary: These lecture notes from a first course in algebraic topology use the fundamental group and orbit categories to classify covering spaces.

entry.title: On the equivariant cohomology of rotation groups and Stiefel manifolds
entry.summary: In this paper, we compute the $RO(\mathbb{Z}/2)$-graded equivariant cohomology of rotation groups and Stiefel manifolds with particular involutions.

entry.title: The Homotopy Theory of Simplicially Enriched Multicategories
entry.summary: In this paper we construct a cofibrantly generated model category structure on the category of all small symmetric multicategories enriched in simplicial sets.

entry.title: Visualizing Poincaré Duality
entry.summary: We investigate some connections between two different ways of defining Poincar\'e Duality, and relate them geometrically to the level curve mapping.

entry.title: A survey on Seifert fiber space conjecture
entry.summary: We recall the history of the proof of Seifert fibre space conjecture, as well as it motivations and its several generalisations.

entry.title: Toric topology
entry.summary: We survey some results on toric topology.
entry.arxiv:comment: English translation of the Japanese article which appeared in "Sugaku" vol. 62 (2010), 386-411

entry.title: On homotopy invariants of finite degree
entry.summary: We prove that homotopy invariants of finite degree distinguish homotopy classes of maps of a connected compact CW-complex to a nilpotent connected CW-complex with finitely generated homotopy groups.

entry.title: Asymptotic Dimension and Boundaries of Hyperbolic Spaces
entry.summary: We give an example of a visual Gromov Hyperbolic metric space X with asdimX=2 and dim(bdry X)=0

entry.title: Dendroidal weak 2-categories
entry.summary: We discuss the dendroidal notion of weak higher categories introduced by Moerdijk and Weiss and we prove that dendroidal weak 2-categories are equivalent to bicategories.

entry.title: The module category weight of compact exceptional Lie groups
entry.summary: We compute the lower bound estimate for the module category weight of compact exceptional Lie groups by analyzing several Eilenberg--Moore type spectral sequences.

entry.title: When is a fourfold Massey product defined?
entry.summary: We define a new invariant in the homology of a differential graded algebra. This invariant is the obstruction to defining a fourfold Massey product.

entry.title: A note on H_infinity structures
entry.summary: We give a source of examples of H_infinity ring structures that do not lift to E_infinity ring structures, based on Mandell's equivalence between certain cochain algebras and spaces.

entry.title: Derived functors of the divided power functors
entry.summary: Some minor changes to the exposition.

entry.title: Generalized edgewise subdivisions
entry.summary: In this paper we classify endofunctors on the simplex category, and we identify those that induce weak equivalence preserving functors on the category of simplicial sets.

entry.title: The monochromatic Hopf invariant
entry.summary: In this paper we will compute the effect of the James-Hopf map after applying the Bousfield-Kuhn functor on Morava E-theory, and then compute the monochromatic Hopf invariant of the $\beta$ family using this cohomological information.

entry.title: Takayasu cofibrations revisited
entry.summary: This note gives a new construction of Takayasu's cofibrations.

entry.title: Jordan s-identities in three variables
entry.summary: It is proved that all Jordan s-identities of the three variables are consequences of s-identities Glennie.

entry.title: On nontriviality of homotopy groups of spheres
entry.summary: For $n\geq 2$, the homotopy groups $\pi_n(S^2)$ are non-zero.

entry.title: Perfect Morse Function on SO(n)
entry.summary: In this work, we define a Morse function on SO(n) and show that this function is indeed a perfect Morse function.

entry.title: The equivariant complex cobordism ring of a finite abelian group
entry.summary: We compute the equivariant (stable) complex cobordism ring $(MU_G)_*$ for finite abelian groups $G$.
entry.arxiv:comment: Accepted for publication in Mathematics Research Letters

entry.title: Symmetric spectra model global homotopy theory of finite groups
entry.summary: We show that the category of symmetric spectra can be used as a model for global equivariant homotopy theory of finite groups.

entry.title: A Relation Between Existence of Real Symmetric Nonsingular Bilinear Maps and the Antisymmetric Index of Projective Spaces
entry.summary: We obtain a new proof, using integral cohomology and group actions, of an old embedding theorem for real projective spaces.

entry.title: Topological Symmetries of R^3
entry.summary: If a finite group acts topologically, faithfully and orientation preservingly on R^3, then it is isomorphic to a subgroup of SO(3).

entry.title: Topological Symmetries of R^3, II
entry.summary: If a fintie group G acts topologically and faithfully on R^3, then G is a subgroup of O(3)

entry.title: The decomposability of smash product of A_n^2-complexes
entry.summary: In this paper, we determine the decomposability of smash product of two indecomposable A_n^2-complexes, i.e., (n-1)-connected finite CW-complexes with dimension at most n+2 (n\geq 3).

entry.title: Topological equivalence to a projection
entry.summary: We present a necessary and sufficient condition for the topological equivalence of a continuous function on a plane to a projection onto one of coordinates.

entry.title: Smallest homotopically trivial non-contractible spaces
entry.summary: We characterize the homotopically trivial non-contractible topological spaces with the minimum number of points.

entry.title: A variation on the homological nerve theorem
entry.summary: An equivalent but useful version on the Homological Nerve Theorem is proved.

entry.title: On the cohomology ring of associated flag bundle
entry.summary: In this expository note, we survey the cohomology rings of flag bundles associated to vector bundles in terms of characteristic classes.

entry.title: Persistent Cohomology of Sheaves
entry.summary: We study a sheaf-theoretical variation of Carlsson and Zomorodian's persistent homology. We apply our techniques to analyze the persistent cellular sheaf cohomology of network coding sheaves on deteriorating networks.

entry.title: On the Bousfield classes of $H_\infty$-ring spectra
entry.summary: We prove that any K(n)-acyclic, $H_\infty$-ring spectrum is K(n+1)-acyclic, affirming an old conjecture of Mark Hovey.

entry.title: Lefschetz duality for intersection (co)homology
entry.summary: We prove the Lefschetz duality for intersection (co)homology in the framework of $\partial$-pesudomanifolds. We work with general perversities and without restriction on the coefficient ring.

entry.title: The symmetrized topological complexity of the circle
entry.summary: We determine the symmetrized topological complexity of the circle, using primarily just general topology.

entry.title: Descent of Deligne-Getzler $\infty$-groupoids
entry.summary: We prove that Getzler's higher generalization of the Deligne groupoid commutes with totalization and homotopy limits.
entry.arxiv:comment: v2: minor corrections. Comments are welcome!

entry.title: Cohomologies of nonassociative metagroup algebras
entry.summary: Cohomologies of nonassociative metagroup algebras are investigated. Extensions of metagroup algebras are studied. Examples are given.

entry.title: Universal Finite Subgroup of Tate Curve
entry.summary: In this paper we construct the universal finite subgroup of Tate curve with quasi-elliptic cohomology and its power operation.

entry.title: Toric manifolds over cyclohedra
entry.summary: We study the action of the dihedral group on the (equivariant) cohomology of the toric manifolds associated with cycle graphs.

entry.title: Intersection forms of almost-flat 4-manifolds
entry.summary: We calculate intersection forms of all 4-dimensional almost-flat manifolds

entry.title: Supplement to the paper "Floating bundles and their applications"
entry.summary: This paper is the supplement to the section 2 of the paper "Floating bundles and their applications" (math.AT/0102054). Below we construct the denumerable set of extensions of the formal group of geometric cobordisms $F(x\otimes 1,1\otimes x)$ by the Hopf algebra $H=\Omega_U^*(Gr).$

entry.title: Homotopy quantum field theory and the index gerbe
entry.summary: Given a family of Dirac operators with vanishing spectral flow we construct a thin-invariant rank-one field theory in the sense of Turner and Willerton arXiv:math.AT/0201116. Our construction of the field theory generalizes the one of the index gerbe by Lott, arXiv:math.DG/0106177, and it also complements the relation between gerbes and thin-invariant rank-one field theories studied in arXive:math.AT/0201116.

entry.title: Generalized Arf invariants in algebraic L-theory
entry.summary: The difference between the quadratic L-groups L_*(A) and the symmetric L-groups L^*(A) of a ring with involution A is detected by generalized Arf invariants. The special case A=Z[x] gives a complete set of invariants for the Cappell UNil-groups UNil_*(Z;Z,Z) for the infinite dihedral group D_{\infty}=Z_2*Z_2, extending the results of Connolly and Ranicki (math.AT/0304016) and Connolly and Davis.

entry.title: Truncated resolution model structures
entry.summary: Using the dual of Bousfield-Friedlander localization we colocalize resolution model structures on cosimplicial objects over a left proper model category to get truncated resolution model structures. These are useful to study realization and moduli problems in algebraic topology.
entry.arxiv:comment: 12 pages, first part of an earlier version of math.AT/0412388 "Interpolation categories for homology theories", to appear in JPAA

entry.title: Chen-Ruan Cohomology of cotangent orbifolds and Chas-Sullivan String Topology
entry.summary: In this paper we prove that for an almost complex orbifold, its virtual orbifold cohomology [math.AT/0606573] is isomorphic as algebras to the Chen-Ruan orbifold cohomology of its cotangent orbifold.

entry.title: The moduli space of generalized Morse functions
entry.summary: We study the moduli and determine a homotopy type of the space of all generalized Morse functions on d-manifolds for given d. This moduli space is closely connected to the moduli space of all Morse functions studied in the paper math.AT/0212321, and the classifying space of the corresponding cobordism category.

entry.title: A canonical enriched Adams-Hilton model for simplicial sets
entry.summary: For any 1-reduced simplicial set $K$ we define a canonical, coassociative coproduct on $\Om C(K)$, the cobar construction applied to the normalized, integral chains on $K$, such that any canonical quasi-isomorphism of chain algebras from $\Om C(K)$ to the normalized, integral chains on $GK$, the loop group of $K$, is a coalgebra map up to strong homotopy. Our proof relies on the operadic description of the category of chain coalgebras and of strongly homotopy coalgebra maps given in math.AT/0505559.
entry.arxiv:comment: 28 pages. This revised version incorporates operadic techniques developed in math.AT/0505559

entry.title: The cohomology of the McLaughlin group and some associated groups
entry.summary: In this paper we compute the mod 2 cohomology of the McLaughlin group, which is one of the sporadic simple groups.

entry.title: The cohomology rings of rank 3 simple groups are Cohen-Macaulay
entry.summary: In this paper we show that the mod 2 cohomology ring of any finite simple group of rank 3 or less (at the prime 2) must be Cohen-Macaulay.

entry.title: On the Homology of Configuration Spaces $C((M,M_o)\times {\bold R}^n; X)$
entry.summary: The homology with coefficients in a field of the configuration spaces $C(M\times \bold R ^n,M_o\times \bold R ^n;X)$ is determined in this paper.

entry.title: Automorphisms and cohomology of discrete groups
entry.summary: In this paper we describe a method for producing elements in the mod p cohomology of a discrete group of finite cohomological dimension. This provides a purely algebraic formulation of the theory of special cycles.
entry.arxiv:comment: author provided postscript file is corrupted

entry.title: The cohomology of the Lyons group and double covers of alternating groups
entry.summary: We compute the mod 2 cohomology of the sporadic simple group Ly as well as that of the double covers of the alternating groups A_8 and A_10.

entry.title: Algebras and modules in monoidal model categories
entry.summary: We construct model category structures for monoids and modules in symmetric monoidal model categories which satisfy an extra axiom, the monoidal axiom, with applications to symmetric spectra and $\Gamma$-spaces.

entry.title: Morava E-theory of symmetric groups
entry.summary: We compute the completed E(n) cohomology of the classifying spaces of the symmetric groups, and relate the answer to the theory of finite subgroups of formal groups.

entry.title: Vanishing lines in Adams spectral sequences are generic
entry.summary: We show that in a generalized Adams spectral sequence, the presence of a vanishing line of fixed slope (at some term of the spectral sequence, with some intercept) is a generic property.

entry.title: On the cohomology of Galois groups determined by Witt rings
entry.summary: Let F denote a field of characteristic different from two. In this paper we describe the mod 2 cohomology of a Galois group which is determined by the Witt ring WF.

entry.title: A degree one Borsuk-Ulam theorem
entry.summary: We observe that the classical Borsuk-Ulam theorem has an easy generalization to maps from an n-manifold M^n to R^n. We point out a geometric corollary.

entry.title: Gross-Hopkins duality
entry.summary: We give a new and simpler proof of a result of Hopkins and Gross relating Brown-Comenetz duality to Spanier-Whitehead duality in the K(n)-local stable homotopy category.

entry.title: Operads and Algebraic Homotopy II. Suspensions
entry.summary: This paper extends the results of "Operads and Algebraic Homotopy" in giving algebraic invariants for the stable homotopy type of a pointed simply-connected simplicial set.

entry.title: Complex cobordism of involutions
entry.summary: We give a simple and explicit presentation of the Z/2-equivariant complex cobordism ring.
entry.arxiv:comment: Published by Geometry and Topology at http://www.maths.warwick.ac.uk/gt/GTVol5/paper11.abs.html

entry.title: On Kan fibrations for Maltsev algebras
entry.summary: We prove that any surjective homomorphism of simplicial Maltsev algebras is a Kan fibration.

entry.title: Secondary Brown-Kervaire Quadratic forms and $π$-manifolds
entry.summary: In this paper we define a secondary Brown-Kervaire quadratic forms. Among the applications we obtain a complete classification of (n-2)-connected 2n-dimensional framed manifolds up to homeomorphism and homotopy equivalence, . In particular, we prove that the homotopy type of such manifolds determine their homeomorphism type.

entry.title: Having the H-space structure is not a generic property
entry.summary: In this note, we answer in negative a question posed by McGibbon about the generic property of H-space structure. In fact we verify the conjecture of Roitberg. Incidentally, the same example also answers in negative the open problem 10 in McGibbon.

entry.title: Mislin genus of maps
entry.summary: In this paper, we prove that the Mislin genus of a (co-)H-map between (co-)H-spaces under certain natural conditions is a finite abelian group which generalizes results in Zabrodsky, McGibbon and Hurvitz

entry.title: Strict model structures for pro-categories
entry.summary: We show that C if is a proper model category, then the pro-category pro-C has a strict model structure in which the weak equivalences are the levelwise weak equivalences. The strict model structure is the starting point for many homotopy theories of pro-objects.

entry.title: On sequences cat (f\sp k)
entry.summary: We prove that, for every decreasing sequence {a \sb k} of natural numbers, there exists a map f: X --> X with cat (f\sp k)=a\sb k.

entry.title: Recognition principle for generalized Eilenberg-Mac Lane spaces
entry.summary: We give a homotopy theoretical characterization of generalized Eilenberg-Mac Lane spaces, modeled after Segal's characterization of infinite loop spaces via Gamma spaces.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Cohomological methods in homotopy theory, Progress in Mathematics, vol. 196, Birkhauser, 2001

entry.title: Detecting Elements and Lusternik--Schnirelmann Category of 3-Manifolds
entry.summary: In this paper, we give a new simplified calculation of the Lusternik-Schnirelmann category of closed 3-manifolds. We also describe when 3-manifolds have detecting elements and prove that 3-manifolds satisfy the equality of the Ganea conjecture.

entry.title: The Lusternik-Schnirelmann Category of Sp(3)
entry.summary: We show that the Lusternik-Schnirelmann category of the symplectic group Sp(3) is 5. This L-S category coincides with the cone length and the stable weak category.

entry.title: Hypercovers in topology
entry.summary: We show that if U is a hypercover of a topological space X then the natural map from hocolim U to X is a weak equivalence. This fact is used to construct topological realization functors for the A^1-homotopy theory of schemes over real and complex fields.

entry.title: Foundations of algebraic surgery
entry.summary: An elementary introduction to the principles of algebraic surgery.
entry.arxiv:comment: 19 pages. Notes of lecture given at the Summer School on High-dimensional Manifold Topology, ICTP Trieste, May-June 2001. To appear in Vol. 1 of the Proceedings

entry.title: Circle valued Morse theory and Novikov homology
entry.summary: An introduction to circle valued Morse theory and Novikov homology, from an algebraic point of view.
entry.arxiv:comment: 26 pages. Notes of lecture given at the Summer School on High-dimensional Manifold Topology, ICTP Trieste, May-June 2001. To appear in Vol. 1 of the Proceedings

entry.title: On the lower bounds for the number of periodic billiard trajectories in manifolds embedded in Euclidean space
entry.summary: In this paper the problem of estimating the number of periodical billiard trajectories is considered. The main result is the theorem on Morse theory for periodical billiard trajectories.

entry.title: Lower bounds for the number of closed billiard trajectories of period 2 and 3 in manifolds embedded in Euclidean space
entry.summary: A lower bound for the number of 3-periodical billiard trajectories in a manifold embedded in Euclidean space is obtained.

entry.title: Equivariant cellular homology and its applications
entry.summary: In this work we develop a cellular equivariant homology functor and apply it to prove an equivariant Euler-Poincare formula and an equivariant Lefschetz theorem.

entry.title: Bar Complexes and Formality of Pull-backs
entry.summary: We prove a result concerning formality of the pull-back of a fibration. Our approach is to use bar complexes in the category of commutative differential graded algebras. As an application, we generalize an old result of Baum and Smith.

entry.title: A note on $H^1(Emb(M,N))$
entry.summary: Aim of this note is to extract cohomological information about the manifold $Emb(M,N)$ from the topology of the target manifold N. For special conditions, a monomorphism $H^1 (N) \to H^1 (Emb(M,N))$ is constructed.

entry.title: Invariants of tangles with flat connections in their complements.I. Invariants and holonomy R-matrices
entry.summary: The notion of holonomy $R$-matrices is introduced. It is shown how to define invariants of tangles with flat connections in a principle $G$-bundle of the complement of a tangle using holonomy $R$-matrices.

entry.title: Invariants of links with flat connections in their complements.II. Holonomy R-matrices related to quantized universal enveloping algebras at roots of 1
entry.summary: Holonomy R-matrices parametrized by finite-dimensional representations are constructed for quantized universal enveloping algebras of simple Lie algebras at roots of 1.

entry.title: A counterexample to a group completion conjecture of JC Moore
entry.summary: We provide a simple explicit counterexample to a group completion conjecture for simplicial monoids attributed to JC Moore.
entry.arxiv:comment: Published by Algebraic and Geometric Topology at http://www.maths.warwick.ac.uk/agt/AGTVol2/agt-2-3.abs.html

entry.title: Cochain operations defining Steenrod $\cup_i$-products in the bar construction
entry.summary: The set of cochain multioperations defining Steenrod $\smile_i$-products in the bar construction is constructed in terms of surjection operad. This structure extends a Homotopy G-algebra structure which defines just the $\cup $ on the bar construction.

entry.title: The Integral Cohomology of the Bianchi Groups
entry.summary: We calculate the integral cohomology ring structure for various members of the Bianchi group family. The main tools we use are the Bockstein spectral sequence and a long exact sequence derived from Bass-Serre theory.

entry.title: Realization of the Stasheff polytope
entry.summary: We propose a simple formula for the coordinates of the vertices of the Stasheff polytope (associahedron) and we compare it to the permutohedron.

entry.title: Equivariant Gysin maps and pulling back fixed points
entry.summary: We develop a new approach to the pulling back fixed point theorem of W. Browder and use it in order to prove various generalizations of this result.

entry.title: Torsion primes in loop space homology
entry.summary: We construct a finite 1-connected CW complex X such that $H_*(\Omega X; Z)$ has p-torsion for the infinitely many primes satisfying p ~ 5,7,17,19 mod 24, but no p-torsion for the infinitely many primes satisfying p ~ 13 or 23 mod 24.

entry.title: L^2-Betti numbers, isomorphism conjectures and noncommutative localization
entry.summary: In this paper we discuss how the question about the rationality of L^2-Betti numbers is related to the Isomorphism Conjecture in algebraic K-theory and why in this context noncommutative localization appears as an important tool.

entry.title: Multiplicative structures on homotopy spectral sequences I
entry.summary: This mostly expository paper records some basic facts about towers of homotopy fiber sequences. We give a proof that a pairing of towers induces a pairing of associated spectral sequences, for towers of spaces and towers of spectra.

entry.title: Evaluation fibrations and topology of symplectomorphisms
entry.summary: There are two main results. The first states that isotropy subgroups of groups acting transitively on a rationally hyperbolic spaces have infinitely generated rational cohomology algebra. Using this fact, we prove that the analogous statement holds for groups of symplectomorphisms of certain blow-ups.

entry.title: Full signature invariants for $L_0(F(t))$
entry.summary: We find full invariants for detecting non--zero elements in ${L}_0(F(t))\otimes \Q$, this group plays an important role in topology in the work done by Casson and Gordon.

entry.title: From $Γ$-spaces to algebraic theories
entry.summary: The paper examines machines of the type of the $\Gamma$-spaces of Segal which describe homotopy structures on topological spaces. The main result of the paper shows that for any such machine one can find an algebraic theory characterizing the same structure on spaces as the original machine.

entry.title: Some examples in toric geometry
entry.summary: We present two examples in toric geometry concerning the relationship between toric and quasitoric manifolds, and provide the sufficient conditions on the base polytope and characteristic map so that the resulting quasitoric manifold is almost complex.

entry.title: Bott towers, crosspolytopes and torus actions
entry.summary: We study the geometry of Bott towers in the context of toric geometry, describing their associated fans arising from crosspolytopes. We compute the cohomology ring of each stage of the tower, and provide all monomial identities defining related affine toric varieties.

entry.title: E-infinity Cell Models for Free and Based Loop Space Cohomology
entry.summary: We construct E-infinity cell algebra models for the cochain algebras of the free and based loop spaces on a simply-connected topological space. Techniques from rational homotopy theory are exploited throughout.

entry.title: Axiomatic stable homotopy - a survey
entry.summary: We survey various approaches to axiomatic stable homotopy theory, with examples including derived categories, categories of (possibly equivariant or localized) spectra, and stable categories of modular representations of finite groups. We focus mainly on representability theorems, localisation, Bousfield classes, and nilpotence.

entry.title: De Rham model for string topology
entry.summary: A De Rham model for string topology based on the theory of iterated integrals is presented.

entry.title: On embeddings in the sphere
entry.summary: We consider embeddings of a finite complex in a sphere. We give a homotopy theoretic classification of such embeddings in a wide range.
entry.arxiv:comment: 13 pages. Revision fixes some typographical errors

entry.title: Split Injectivity of the Baum-Connes Assembly Map
entry.summary: In this work, the continuously controlled techniques developed by Carlsson and Pedersen are used to prove that the Baum-Connes map is a split injection for groups satisfying certain geometric conditions.

entry.title: Configuration spaces are not homotopy invariant
entry.summary: We present a counterexample to the conjecture on the homotopy invariance of configuration spaces. More precisely, we consider the lens spaces $L_{7,1}$ and $L_{7,2}$, and prove that their configuration spaces are not homotopy equivalent by showing that their universal coverings have different Massey products.

entry.title: Cobordism group of Morse functions on unoriented surfaces
entry.summary: The computation of the cobordism group of Morse functions on unoriented surfaces using Stein factorizations.

entry.title: Toroidal orbifolds, gerbes and group cohomology
entry.summary: We compute the integral cohomology of certain semi-direct products arising from a linear G-action on the n-torus, where G is a finite group. The main application is the complete calculation of torsion gerbes for certain six dimensional examples arising from string theory.

entry.title: Smith Theory for algebraic varieties
entry.summary: We show how an approach to Smith Theory about group actions on CW-complexes using Bredon cohomology can be adapted to work for algebraic varieties.
entry.arxiv:comment: Published by Algebraic and Geometric Topology at http://www.maths.warwick.ac.uk/agt/AGTVol4/agt-4-8.abs.html

entry.title: Relative mapping class group of $S^p\times D^q$
entry.summary: Algebraic structure of the group of pseudo-isotopy classes of diffeomorphisms of the trivial disk bundle over the standard sphere which restrict to the identity map on the boundary is determined.

entry.title: A model structure a la Thomason on 2-Cat
entry.summary: We exhibit a model structure on 2-Cat, obtained by transfer from sSet across the adjunction C_2 o Sd^2 -| Ex^2 o N_2.

entry.title: An alternative approach to homotopy operations
entry.summary: We give a particular choice of the higher Eilenberg-MacLane maps by a recursive formula.This choice leads to a simple description of the homotopy operations for simplicial Z/2-algebras.

entry.title: A retraction theorem for topological fundamental groups with application to the Hawaiian earring
entry.summary: A characterization of regular topological fundamental groups yields a `no retraction theorem' for spaces constructed in similar fashion to the Hawaiian earring.

entry.title: Bordism between Dold and Milnor Manifolds
entry.summary: It is well known that Dold and Milnor manifolds give generators for the unoriented bordism algebra ${\frak{N}}_*$ over ${\Bbb{Z}}_2$. The purpose of this paper is to determine those Milnor manifolds which represent the same bordism classes in ${\frak{N}}_*$ as their Dold counterparts.

entry.title: Cohomology operations and the Deligne conjecture
entry.summary: The aim of this note, which raises more questions than it answers, is to study natural operations acting on the cohomology of various types of algebras. It contains a lot of very surprising partial results and examples.

entry.title: The Extension of Knot Groups to Tangles
entry.summary: The extension of the knot group $\pi_1(S^3\setminus K)$ to the category of tangles is introduced via a new category-theoretic construction. Through this presentation, a new avenue of proof for results about knot groups is opened.

entry.title: The classification of 2-compact groups (talk summary)
entry.summary: This is a summary of a talk given at the "Conference on Pure and Applied Topology", Isle of Skye, June 24, 2005. It contains an announcement and sketch of proof of the classification of 2-compact groups.

entry.title: Parking functions and triangulation of the associahedron
entry.summary: We show that a minimal triangulation of the associahedron (Stasheff polytope) of dimension n is made of (n+1)^{n-1} simplices. We construct a natural bijection with the set of parking functions from a new interpretation of parking functions in terms of shuffles.

entry.title: The homotopy type of the complement of the codimension-two coordinate subspace arrangement
entry.summary: The complement of the codimension 2 complex coordinate subspace arrangement is shown to be homotopy equivalent to a wedge of spheres.

entry.title: Operads and PROPs
entry.summary: We review definitions and basic properties of operads, PROPs and algebras over these structures.
entry.arxiv:comment: 49 pages, to appear in Handbook of Algebra. More citations added

entry.title: Equivariant evaluation subgroups and Rhodes groups
entry.summary: In this paper, we define equivariant evaluation subgroups of the higher Rhodes groups and study their relations with Gottlieb-Fox groups.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Cah. Topol. G\'eom. Diff\'er. Cat\'eg. 48 (2007), no. 1, 55--69

entry.title: Cobounding odd cycle colorings
entry.summary: We give a very short self-contained combinatorial proof of the Babson-Kozlov conjecture, by presenting a cochain whose coboundary is the desired power of the characteristic class.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Electron. Res. Announc. Amer. Math. Soc. 12 (2006), 53-55.

entry.title: Classification spaces of maps in model categories
entry.summary: This paper corrects a small mistake in a paper of Dwyer-Kan, and uses this to identify homotopy function complexes in a model category with the nerves of certain categories of zig-zags.
entry.arxiv:comment: updated references, minor changes in terminology

entry.title: Corrections to: Involutions fixing $\Bbb{RP}^{\text{odd}}\sqcup P(h,i)$, II
entry.summary: The purpose of this note is to correct statements of some assertions in \cite{l}.

entry.title: Configuration spaces and R^n
entry.summary: This note attempts to make clear the relation between configurations of points in a space Y and those in its Cartesian product with the reals. We show that under certain conditions there is an equivalence between C(Y x R^n, X) and the n-th loop space of C(Y,S^n(X)).

entry.title: Comparing Singular Homology with respect to Isometry
entry.summary: This article was withdrawn by the arXiv.org administrators since it plagiarizes math.AT/0401211.
entry.arxiv:comment: This article was withdrawn by the arXiv.org administrators since it plagiarizes math.AT/0401211

entry.title: Coincidence theory in arbitrary codimensions: the minimizing problem
entry.summary: Coincidences of maps between smooth manifolds are studied via a geometric approach which involves (nonstabilized) normal bordism theory and pathspaces.

entry.title: Modules in Monoidal Model Categories
entry.summary: This paper studies the existence of and compatibility between derived change of ring, balanced product, and function module derived functors on module categories in monoidal model categories.

entry.title: Groupoids, the Phragmen-Brouwer Property and the Jordan Curve Theorem
entry.summary: We publicise a proof of the Jordan Curve Theorem which relates it to the Phragmen-Brouwer Property, and whose proof uses the van Kampen theorem for the fundamental groupoid on a set of base points.
entry.arxiv:comment: to be published in "Journal of Homotopy and Related Structures"

entry.title: Pro-torus actions on Poincaré duality spaces
entry.summary: In this paper, it is shown that some of the results of torus actions on Poincar\'{e} duality spaces, Borel's dimension formula and topological splitting principle to local weights, hold if `torus' is replaced by `pro-torus'.

entry.title: Fundamental Groups of Commuting Elements in Lie Groups
entry.summary: We compute the fundamental group of the spaces of ordered commuting $n$-tuples of elements in the Lie groups SU(2), U(2) and SO(3). For SO(3) the computation of the mod-2 cohomology of the components of these spaces is also obtained.

entry.title: Spectra for commutative algebraists
entry.summary: The article is designed to explain to commutative algebraists what spectra (in the sense of algebraic topology) are, why they were originally defined, and how they can be useful for commutative algebra.
entry.arxiv:comment: To appear in the proceedings of the summer school "Interactions between homotopy theory and algebra" (Chicago, 2004)

entry.title: Lectures on the Cohomology of Finite Groups
entry.summary: In this paper we first survey some basic results in the cohomology of finite groups, and then discuss recent work on constructing free actions of finite groups on products of spheres.
entry.arxiv:comment: To appear in the proceedings of the summer school "Interactions between homotopy theory and algebra" (Chicago, 2004)

entry.title: Asymptotic Dimension of Finitely Presented Groups
entry.summary: It is proven that if a finitely presented group is one ended it has asymptotic dimension bigger than one. It follows that finitely presented groups with asdim 1 are virtually free. A counterexample is given for the finitely generated case.

entry.title: The homotopy theory of equivalence relations
entry.summary: We give a detailed exposition of the homotopy theory of equivalence relations, perhaps the simplest nontrivial example of a model structure.
entry.arxiv:comment: A few minor improvements in version 2

entry.title: On ring-valued invariants of topological pairs
entry.summary: Based on the notion of a $\Delta$-group(oid), ring-valued invariants of pairs of topological spaces can be defined in intrinsic topological terms.
entry.arxiv:comment: 5 pages, no figures, Theorem 1 has been removed, some corrections added

entry.title: A note on spaces of symmetric matrices
Cobordism realizations of Thom polynomials of singularities
entry.summary: We define complex cobordism realizations of cohomological Thom polynomials and study their existence, uniqueness and other features. We show that problem is non-trivial on the example of $\Sigma^1$ singularity.

entry.title: Compatible Actions and Cohomology of Crystallographic Groups
entry.summary: We compute the cohomology of crystallographic groups with holonomy of prime order. As an application we compute the group of gerbes associated to many six--dimensional toroidal orbifolds arising in string theory.

entry.title: Derived completions in stable homotopy theory
entry.summary: We construct a notion of derived completion which applies to homomorphisms of commutative S-algebras. We study the relationship of the construction with other constructions of completions, and prove various invariance properties. The construction is expected to have applications within algebraic K-theory.

entry.title: On the Dreaded Right Bousfield Localization
entry.summary: I verify the existence of right Bousfield localizations of right semimodel categories, and I apply this to construct a model of the homotopy limit of a left Quillen presheaf as a right semimodel category.

entry.title: Twisting Elements in Homotopy G-algebras
entry.summary: We study the notion of twisting elements $da=a\cup_1a$ with respect to $\cup_1$ product when it is a part of homotopy Gerstenhaber algebra structure. This allows to bring to one context the two classical concepts, the theory of deformation of algebras of M. Gerstenhaber, and $A(\infty)$-algebras of J. Stasheff.

entry.title: Classification problems of toric manifolds via topology
entry.summary: We propose some problems on the classification of toric manifolds from the viewpoint of topology and survey related results.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proc. of Toric Topology, Contemp. Math. 460 (2008), 273-286

entry.title: Homotopy nilpotency in p-compact groups
entry.summary: A p-compact group is a mod p homotopy theoretical analogue of a compact Lie group. It is determined the homotopy nilpotency class of a p-compact group having the homotopy type of the $p$-completion of the direct product of spheres.

entry.title: Poincaré duality for $K$-theory of equivariant complex projective spaces
entry.summary: We make explicit Poincar\'{e} duality for the equivariant $K$-theory of equivariant complex projective spaces. The case of the trivial group provides a new approach to the $K$-theory orientation.

entry.title: Smooth parametrized torsion -- a manifold approach
entry.summary: We give a construction of a torsion invariant of bundles of smooth manifolds which is based on the work of Dwyer, Weiss and Williams on smooth structures on fibrations.

entry.title: 3-groups are not determined by their integral cohomology rings
entry.summary: We compute the integral cohomology rings of a family of 3-groups. As a corollary, we exhibit, for each n greater than or equal to 5, a pair of groups of order 3^n whose integral cohomology rings are isomorphic.

entry.title: Homotopy theory of modules over operads and non-Sigma operads in monoidal model categories
entry.summary: This paper studies the existence of model category structures on algebras and modules over operads in monoidal model categories.

entry.title: Classification of certain cellular classes of chain complexes
entry.summary: Let (R, m) be a local commutative ring. Suppose that m is principal and that m^2 = 0. We give a complete description of the cellular lattice of perfect chain complexes of modules over this ring.

entry.title: Convergence of the Eilenberg-Moore spectral sequence for generalized cohomology theories
entry.summary: We prove that the Morava-$K$-theory-based Eilenberg-Moore spectral sequence has good convergence properties whenever the base space is a $p$-local finite Postnikov system with vanishing $(n+1)$st homotopy group.

entry.title: Decompositions involving Anick's spaces
entry.summary: Recently Stephen Theriault and I found an elementary construction of Anick's spaces and proved their main properties(arXiv:0710.1024).In this work the fundamental fibration is decomposed. This is useful in studying maps out of Anick's spaces and will be needed in order to determine it's universal properties.

entry.title: Classifying Dihedral O(2)-Equivariant Spectra
entry.summary: The category of rational O(2)-equivariant spectra splits as a product of cyclic and dihedral parts. Using the classification of rational G-equivariant spectra for finite groups G, we classify the dihedral part of rational O(2)-equivariant spectra in terms of an algebraic model.

entry.title: On the homotopy theory of spectral categories
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn by the author, due a critical mistake on page 3.

entry.title: Homological stability of non-orientable mapping class groups with marked points
entry.summary: Wahl recently proved that the homology of the non-orientable mapping class group stabilizes as the genus increases. In this short note we analyse the situation where the underlying non-orientable surfaces have marked points.
entry.arxiv:comment: 8 pages, 1 figure, to appear in Proc. AMS

entry.title: Correction to "Simplicial monoids and Segal categories"
entry.summary: In this note we make a minor correction to the paper ``Simplicial monoids and Segal categories."
entry.arxiv:comment: 3 pages, minor correction to the indicated paper which has already been published

entry.title: Motion planning in spaces with small fundamental group
entry.summary: We establish sharp upper bounds for the topological complexity of motion planning problem in spaces with small fundamental group, i.e. when it is finite of small order or has small cohomological dimension.

entry.title: The String bordism of $BE_8$ and $BE_8\times BE_8$ through dimension 14
entry.summary: We compute the low dimensional String bordism groups of $BE_8$ and $BE_8\times BE_8$ using a combination of Adams spectral sequences together with comparisons to the Spin bordism cases.

entry.title: A note on localizations of mapping spaces
entry.summary: We show that if A is a simply connected, finite, pointed CW-complex then the mapping spaces Map(A, -) are preserved by the localization functors only if A has the rational homotopy type of a wedge of spheres of a fixed dimension.

entry.title: Chains on suspension spectra
entry.summary: We define and study a homological version of Sullivan's rational de Rham complex for simplicial sets. This new functor can be generalised to simplicial symmetric spectra and in that context it has excellent categorical properties which promise to make a number of interesting applications much more straightforward.

entry.title: The spectra ko and ku are not Thom spectra: an approach using THH
entry.summary: We apply an announced result of Blumberg-Cohen-Schlichtkrull to reprove (under restricted hypotheses) a theorem of Mahowald: the connective real and complex K-theory spectra are not Thom spectra.

entry.title: Chern subrings
entry.summary: Let p be an odd prime. We show that for a simply-connected semisimple complex linear algebraic group, if its integral homology has p-torsion, the Chern classes do not generate the Chow ring of its classifying space.

entry.title: Thom spectra that are symmetric spectra
entry.summary: We analyze the functorial and multiplicative properties of the Thom spectrum functor in the setting of symmetric spectra, and we establish the relevant homotopy invariance.

entry.title: A streamlined proof of Goodwillie's n-excisive approximation
entry.summary: We give a shorter proof of Lemma 1.9 from Goodwillie, "Calculus III", which is the key step in proving that the construction P_nF gives an n-excisive functor.

entry.title: Comparison of Morava E-theories
entry.summary: In this note we show that the n-th Morava E-cohomology group of a finite spectrum with action of the n-th Morava stabilizer group can be recovered from the (n+1)-st Morava E-cohomology group with action of the (n+1)-st Morava stabilizer group.

entry.title: The cyclotomic trace for symmetric ring spectra
entry.summary: The purpose of this paper is to present a simple and explicit construction of the Bokstedt-Hsiang-Madsen cyclotomic trace relating algebraic K-theory and topological cyclic homology. Our construction also incorporates Goodwillie's idea of a global cyclotomic trace.

entry.title: On the classification of unstable H*V-A-modules
entry.summary: In this work, we begin studying the classification, up to isomorphism, of unstable H*V-A-modules E such that the tensor product of F_2 and E over H*V is isomorphic to a given unstable A-module.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Journal of Homotopy and Related Structures vol4 (1), 2009 pp63-76

entry.title: Improved homological stability for the mapping class group with integral or twisted coefficients
entry.summary: In this paper we prove stability results for the homology of the mapping class group of a surface. We get a stability range that is near optimal, and extend the result to twisted coefficients.

entry.title: Realizing Families of Landweber Exact Homology Theories
entry.summary: I discuss the problem of realizing families of complex orientable homology theories as families of commutative ring spectra, including a recent result of Jacob Lurie emphasizing the role of p-divisible groups.

entry.title: A theorem of Poincaré-Hopf type
entry.summary: We compute (algebraically) the Euler characteristic of a complex of sheaves with constructible cohomology. A stratified Poincar\'e-Hopf formula is then a consequence of the smooth Poincar\'e-Hopf theorem and of additivity of the Euler-Poincar\'e characteristic with compact supports, once we have a suitable definition of index.

entry.title: Higher homotopy operations and cohomology
entry.summary: We explain how higher homotopy operations, defined topologically, may be identified under mild assumptions with (the last of) the Dwyer-Kan-Smith cohomological obstructions to rectifying homotopy-commutative diagrams.

entry.title: Equivariant Twisted Cartan Cohomology Theory
entry.summary: In this note we prove an equivariant version of a result of Cartan for equivariant simplicial cohomology with local coefficients.
entry.arxiv:comment: 14 pages, some typos and minor changes.

entry.title: A Freeness Theorem for RO(Z/2)-graded Cohomology
entry.summary: In this paper it is shown that the RO(Z/2)-graded cohomology of a certain class of Rep(Z/2)-complexes, which includes projective spaces and Grassmann manifolds, is always free as a module over the cohomology of a point when the coefficient Mackey functor is \underline{Z/2}.

entry.title: Autour des résultats d'annulation cohomologique de Scorichenko
entry.summary: The ain of this note is to make available the unpublished proof of Scorichenko of the isomorphism between stable K-theory and functor homology for polynomial coefficients over an arbitrary ring.

entry.title: Cohomology Rings of Precubical Sets
entry.summary: The aim of this paper is to define the structure of a ring on a graded cohomology group of a precubical set in coefficients in a ring with unit.

entry.title: Embedding the flag representation in divided powers
entry.summary: A generalization of a theorem of Crabb and Hubbuck concerning the embedding of flag representations in divided powers is given, working over an arbitrary finite field F, using the category of functors from finite-dimensional F-vector spaces to F-vector spaces.

entry.title: The kernel of the Magnus representation of the automorphism group of a free group is not finitely generated
entry.summary: In this paper, we show that the abelianization of the kernel of the Magnus representation of the automorphism group of a free group is not finitely generated.

entry.title: On Generalized Whitehead Products
entry.summary: A symmetric monoidal pairing is defined among simply connected co-H spaces and this is used to generalize the Whitehead product map S(X ^ Y) --> SX v SY to co-H spaces.

entry.title: The integral cohomology ring of E_8/T^1E_7
entry.summary: We determine the integral cohomology ring of the homogeneous space E_8/T^1E_7 by the Borel presentation and a method due to Toda. Then using the Gysin exact sequence associated with the circle bundle S^1 -> E_8/E_7 -> E_8/T^1E_7, we also determine the integral cohomology of E_8/E_7.

entry.title: Topological Complexity and non-immersions of real projective space
entry.summary: This article has been withdrawn due to an error in a proof of the main result.

entry.title: The Arf-Kervaire Invariant of framed manifolds
entry.summary: This work surveys classical and recent advances around the existence of exotic differentiable structures on spheres and its connection to stable homotopy theory.

entry.title: A proof of Halperin-Carlsson Conjecture for free Z_2-torus actions on manifolds
entry.summary: This paper has been withdrawn due to a gap in the proof of the main result.
entry.arxiv:comment: This paper has been withdrawn due to a gap in the proof of the main result.

entry.title: The algebra of rack and quandle cohomology
entry.summary: In this paper we describe methods for computing rack and quandle cohomology. We illustrate these methods by completely determining the cohomology of prime dihedral quandles.

entry.title: The HELP-Lemma and its converse in Quillen model categories
entry.summary: We show that a map between fibrant objects in a closed model category is a weak equivalence if and only if it has the right homotopy extension lifting property with respect to all cofibrations. The dual statement holds for maps between cofibrant objects.

entry.title: On moduli subspaces of central extensions of rational H-spaces
entry.summary: We investigate the moduli sets of central extensions of H-spaces enjoying inversivity, power associativity and Moufang properties. By considering rational H-extensions, it turns out that there is no relationship between the first and the second properties in general.

entry.title: Braided bialgebras in a generated monoidal Ab-category
entry.summary: We start from any small strict monoidal braided Ab-category and extend it to a monoidal nonstrict braided Ab-category which contains braided bialgebras. The objects of the original category turn out to be modules for these bialgebras

entry.title: Geometric approach to stable homotopy groups of spheres, III. Abelian, cyclic and quaternionic structure for mappings with singularities
entry.summary: Collection of (equivariant) $\rm{PL}$-mappings admitting a relative abelian, cyclic, quaternionic, bicyclic, and quaternionic-cyclic structures are constructed.

entry.title: A remark on the homotopy equivalence of SU_n and SL_nC
entry.summary: Being a maximal compact subgroup of SL_nC, SU_n is a deformation retract of the former group. In this note we prove that, for sufficiently large n, there is no retraction of SL_nC to SU_n which preserves commutativity.

entry.title: On the ku-homology of certain classifying spaces II
entry.summary: We calculate the annihilator of the ku-toral class for the p-groups Z_{p^2} X Z_{p^k}$ with k > 2. This allows us to give a description of the ku-homology of these groups.

entry.title: The fiber homotopically equivalent relation for fiber bundles
entry.summary: In this paper, we will give the polyhedron property role to satisfy fiber homotopically equivalent relation in fiber bundle theory over suspensions of polyhedron space.

entry.title: On the cohomology of classifying spaces of groups of homeomorphisms
entry.summary: Let M be a closed simply connected 2n-dimensional manifold. The present paper is concerned with the cohomology of classifying spaces of connected groups of homeomorphisms of M.

entry.title: A Finite Dimensional $A_{\infty}$ Algebra Example
entry.summary: We construct an example of an $A_{\infty}$ algebra structure defined over a finite dimensional graded vector space.

entry.title: Oriented Cobordism of $\CP^{2k+1}$
entry.summary: We give a new construction of oriented manifolds having the boundary $\CC P^{2k+1}$ for each $k \geq 0$. The main tool is the theory of quasitoric manifolds.
entry.arxiv:comment: 9 pages, 5 gigures, Section 6 is deleted for a crucial error

entry.title: Constructing free actions of p-groups on products of spheres
entry.summary: We prove that, for p an odd prime, every finite p-group of rank 3 acts freely on a finite complex X homotopy equivalent to a product of three spheres.

entry.title: Decompositions of looped co-H-spaces and applications
entry.summary: We prove two homotopy decomposition theorems for the loops on co-H-spaces, including a generalization of the Hilton-Milnor Theorem. These are applied to problems arising in algebra, representation theory, toric topology, and the study of quasi-symmetric functions.

entry.title: Relative categories: Another model for the homotopy theory of homotopy theories
entry.summary: We lift Charles Rezk's complete Segal space model structure on the category of simplicial spaces to a Quillen equivalent one on the category of relative categories.
entry.arxiv:comment: 27 pages. Updated to correct typographical errors

entry.title: Rational Z_p-Equivariant Spectra
entry.summary: We find a simple algebraic model for rational G-equivariant spectra, where G is the p-adic integers, via a series of Quillen equivalences. This model, along with an Adams short exact sequence, will allow us to easily perform constructions and calculations.

entry.title: More examples of motivic cell structures
entry.summary: In this note, we describe motivic cell structures arising from the Bialynicki-Birula decomposition. This provides a description of the stable A^1-homotopy types of smooth projective G_m-varieties where the G_m-action has isolated fixed points.

entry.title: Relations among tautological classes revisited
entry.summary: We give a simple generalisation of a theorem of Morita, which leads to a great number of relations among tautological classes on moduli spaces of curves.

entry.title: A characterization of simplicial localization functors
entry.summary: We characterize simplicial localization functors among relative functors from relative categories to simplicial categories as any choice of homotopy inverse to the delocalization functor of Dwyer and the second author.

entry.title: A Lefschetz duality intersection homology
entry.summary: We prove a Lefschetz duality result for intersection homology. Usually, this result applies to pseudomanifolds with boundary which are assumed to have a "collared neighborhood of their boundary". Our duality does not need this assumption and is a generalization of the classical one.

entry.title: On quadratic coalgebras, duality and the universal Steenrod algebra
entry.summary: The notion of quadratic self-duality for coalgebras is developed with applications to algebraic structures which arise naturally in algebraic topology, related to the universal Steenrod algebra via an appropriate form of duality. This explains and unifies results of Lomonaco and Singer.

entry.title: A Thomason-like Quillen equivalence between quasi-categories and relative categories
entry.summary: We describe a Quillen equivalence between quasi-categories and relative categories which is surprisingly similar to Thomason's Quillen equivalences between simplicial sets and categories.

entry.title: On spherical classes in $H_*QX$
entry.summary: We give an upper bound on the set of spherical classes in $H_*QX$ when $X = P,S^1$. This is related to the Curtis conjecture on spherical classes in $H_*Q_0S^0$. The results also provide some control over the bordism classes on of immersions when $X$ is a Thom complex.

entry.title: Scissors Congruence as K-theory
entry.summary: Scissors congruence groups have traditionally been expressed algebraically in terms of group homology. We give an alternate construction of these groups by producing them as the $0$-level in the algebraic $K$-theory of a Waldhausen category.

entry.title: Homotopical exact squares and derivators
entry.summary: The aim of this paper is to generalize in a homotopical framework the notion of exact square introduced by Ren\'e Guitart, and explain the relationship between this generalization and the theory of derivators.

entry.title: A Quillen theorem Bn for homotopy pullbacks
entry.summary: We prove an extension of the Quillen Theorem Bn for homotopy fibres to a similar result for homotopy pullbacks and use this to obtain sufficient conditions on a pullback diagram of categories to guarantee that it be a homotopy pullback.

entry.title: n-Relative Categories
entry.summary: We introduce, for every positive integer n, the notion of an n-relative category and show that the category of the small n-relative categories is a model for the homotopy theory of n-fold homotopy theories, i.e. homotopy theories of ... of homotopy theories.

entry.title: Toric Topology. Chapter 2: Combinatorial structures
entry.summary: This is the second chapter in our "Toric Topology" book project. Further chapters are coming. Comments and suggestions are very welcome.
entry.arxiv:comment: Current version of the book is now available as arXiv:1210.2368

entry.title: Toda brackets and congruences of modular forms
entry.summary: This paper investigates the relation between Toda brackets and congruences of modular forms. It determines the $f$-invariant of Toda brackets and thereby generalizes the formulas of J.F.\ Adams for the classical $e$-invariant to the chromatic second filtration.

entry.title: Poincare' series for maximal De Concini-Procesi models of root arrangements
entry.summary: In this paper we focus on maximal complex De Concini-Procesi models associated to root arrangements of types A, B, C, D and we compute inductive formulas for their Poincare' series.

entry.title: The Gromov-Lawson-Rosenberg conjecture for the Semi-Dihedral group of order 16
entry.summary: We show that the Gromov-Lawson-Rosenberg conjecture for the Semi-Dihedral group of order 16 is true.

entry.title: Homology decompositions and groups inducing fusion systems
entry.summary: We relate the construction of groups which realize saturated fusion systems and signaliser functors with homology decompositions of p-local finite groups. We prove that the cohomology ring of Robinson's construction is in some precise sense very close to the cohomology ring of the fusion system it realizes.

entry.title: On the anti-automorphism of the Steenrod algebra: II
entry.summary: The relations of Barratt and Miller are shown to include all relations among the elements $P^i\chi P^{n-i}$ in the mod $p$ Steenrod algebra, and a minimal set of relations is given.

entry.title: Abelian varieties and the Kervaire invariant
entry.summary: Notes from a talk at the April 2011 ICMS (Edinburgh) conference on the recent solution of the Kervaire invariant problem. This is an entirely expository account, emphasizing connections with the theory of topological automorphic forms.

entry.title: A simple homotopy-theoretical proof of the Sullivan conjecture
entry.summary: We give a new proof, using comparatively simple techniques, of the Sullivan conjecture: the space of pointed maps from the classifying space of the cyclic group of order $p$ to any finite-dimensional CW complex $K$ is contractible.

entry.title: Topological complexity of the telescope
entry.summary: We use an alternative definition of topological complexity to show that the topological complexity of the mapping telescope of a sequence $X_1\rightarrow X_2\rightarrow X_3\rightarrow...$ is bounded above by $2max{TC(X_i); i=1,2,...}$.

entry.title: Compactly generated quasitopological homotopy groups with discontinuous multiplication
entry.summary: For each positive integer Q there exists a path connected metric compactum X such that the Qth-homotopy group of X is compactly generated but not a topological group (with the quotient topology).

entry.title: Chern classes and generators
entry.summary: We give a simple proof for the fact that algebra generators of the mod 2 cohomology of classifying spaces of exceptional Lie groups are given by Chern classes and Stiefel-Whitney classes of certain representations.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proc. Japan Acad. Ser. A Math. Sci. 88(1) (2010) 21-23

entry.title: A model for the Whitehead product in rational mapping spaces
entry.summary: We describe the Whitehead products in the rational homotopy group of a connected component of a mapping space in terms of the Andr\'{e}-Quillen cohomology. As a consequence, an upper bound for the Whitehead length of a mapping space is given.

entry.title: String-net model of Turaev-Viro invariants
entry.summary: In this paper, we describe the relation between the Turaev--Viro TQFT and the string-net space introduced in the papers of Levin and Wen. In particular, the case of surfaces with boundary is considered in detail.

entry.title: Simplicial Homeology and Homeotopy
entry.summary: In this paper, we define homeology group, reduced homeology group, cohomeology group and reduced cohomeology group on finite simpicial complexes and prove that these groups are homeomorphism invariants of polyhedra. We also define homeotopy type of polyhedra which is finer than homotopy type but coarser than homeomorphism class.

entry.title: On resolutions of diagrams of algebras
entry.summary: We prove a restricted version of a conjecture by M. Markl on resolutions of an operad describing diagrams of algebras. We discuss a particular case related to the Gerstenhaber-Schack diagram cohomology.

entry.title: Homotopy groups as centers of finitely presented groups
entry.summary: For every finite abelian group $A$ and $n\geq 3$, we construct a finitely presented group defined by explicit generators and relations, such that its center is $\pi_n(\Sigma K(A,1))$.

entry.title: The homology of simpicial complements and the cohomology of moment-angle complexes
entry.summary: We use the Taylor resolution of a monomial ideal to compute the Tor algebra of the Stanley-Reisner ring of a simplicial complement of a simplicial complex.

entry.title: An elementary proof of the string topology structure of compact oriented surfaces
entry.summary: We give a new proof of the string topology structure of a compact oriented surface of genus g greater than or equal to 2, using elementary algebraic topology. This reproves the result of Vaintrob.

entry.title: Almost Complex Structures on (n-1)-connected 2n-manifolds
entry.summary: Let M be a closed (n-1)-connected 2n-dimensional smooth manifold with n > 2. In terms of the system of invariants for such manifolds introduced by Wall, we obtain necessary and sufficient conditions for M to admit an almost complex structure.

entry.title: A Model Structure on the Category of Topological Categories
entry.summary: In this article, we construct a cofibrantly generated Quillen model structure on the category of small topological categories $\mathbf{Cat}_{\mathbf{Top}}$. It is Quillen equivalent to the Joyal model structure of $(\infty,1)$-categories and the Bergner model structure on $\mathbf{Cat}_{\mathbf{sSet}}$.

entry.title: The total Betti number of the intersection of three real quadrics
entry.summary: We prove that the total Betti number of the intersection X of three quadrics in RP^n is bounded by n(n+1). This bound improves the classical Barvinok's one which is at least of order three in n.

entry.title: A model categorical approach to group completion of E_n-algebras
entry.summary: A group completion functor Q is constructed in the category of algebras in simplicial sets over a cofibrant E_n-operad M. It is shown that Q defines a Bousfield-Friedander simplicial model category on M-algebras.

entry.title: A Filtration of Unoriented Cobordism
entry.summary: We give a filtration of the unoriented cobordism ring using the infinite symplectic group, with polynomial generators given one at a time. The generating manifolds are also constructed using the cup construction.

entry.title: Computing Adem Cohomology Operations
entry.summary: We deal with the problem of obtaining explicit simplicial formulae defining the classical Adem cohomology operations at the cochain level. Having these formulae at hand, we design an algorithm for computing these operations for any finite simplicial set.

entry.title: A Dirac Morphism for the Farrell-Jones Isomorphism Conjecture in K-Theory
entry.summary: We construct a Dirac morphism and prove that if this Dirac morphism is invertible, then the isomorphism conjecture for non-connective algebraic K-theory holds true.

entry.title: Cohomology mod 3 of the classifying space of the exceptional Lie group $E_6$, II : The Weyl group invariants
entry.summary: We calculate the Weyl group invariants with respect to a maximal torus of the exceptional Lie group $E_6$.

entry.title: Broad posets, trees, and the dendroidal category
entry.summary: An extension of order theory is presented that serves as a formalism for the study of dendroidal sets analogously to way the formalism of order theory is used in the study of simplicial sets.

entry.title: The homology coalgebra and cohomology algebra of generalized moment-angle complexes
entry.summary: In this paper, we compute the homology coalgebra and cohomology algebra over a field of all generalized moment-angle complexes and give a duality theorem on complementary moment-angle complexes.

entry.title: Euler Calculus with Applications to Signals and Sensing
entry.summary: This article surveys the Euler calculus - an integral calculus based on Euler characteristic - and its applications to data, sensing, networks, and imaging.
entry.arxiv:comment: 71 pages, 31 figures, AMS Proceedings of Symposia in Applied Mathematics

entry.title: On the splitting of polynomial functors
entry.summary: We develop methods for proving that certain extensions of polynomial functors do not split naturally. As an application we give a functorial description of the third and the fourth stable homotopy groups of the classifying spaces of free abelian groups.

entry.title: A geometric view of the Chern character
entry.summary: In this note we show that the Chern character form of a superconnection is obtained via the parallel transport of the superconnection along superpaths, by restriction to the universal superpoint path.

entry.title: On fibrations with flat fibers
entry.summary: We describe pairs (p,n) such that n-dimensional affine space is fibered by pairwise skew p-dimensional affine subspaces. The problem is closely related with the theorem of Adams on vector fields on spheres and the Hurwitz-Radon theory of composition of quadratic forms.

entry.title: On the connectivity of finite subset spaces
entry.summary: We show that for an m-connected cell complex X the space exp_k X of non-empty subsets of X of cardinality at most k is (m + k - 2)-connected

entry.title: Context-free manifold calculus and the Fulton-MacPherson Operad
