entry.summary: The paper gives an explicit description of the Weiss embedding tower in terms of spaces of maps of truncated modules over the framed Fulton-MacPherson operad.

entry.title: S^1-equivariant Morse cohomology
entry.summary: We construct a deformed Morse complex computing the equivariant cohomology of a manifold M endowed with a smooth S^1-action. The deformation of the coboundary operator is given by counting gradient flow lines of a Morse function f that are allowed to "jump" along orbits of the S^1-action for finite time intervalls.

entry.title: Classification of compact real surfaces: a quick proof
entry.summary: The aim of this note is to give a quick algebraic proof of (the combinatorial part of) the classification theorem for compact real surfaces, whose classical proofs (as in the Massey book and in the Conway ZIP proof) are based on surgery (and pictures) and look more intricate.

entry.title: On Lusternik-Schnirelmann Category of Connected Sums
entry.summary: In this paper we estimate the Lusternik-Schnirelmann category of the connected sum of two manifolds through their categories. We achieve a more general result regarding the category of a quotient space X/A where A is a suitable subspace of X.

entry.title: An abelian embedding for Moore spectra
entry.summary: We embed the category of Moore spectra as a full subcategory of an abelian category, and make some remarks about abelian embeddings of various other categories of spectra.

entry.title: A Short Note on Mapping Cylinders
entry.summary: Given a homotopy equivalence f between two topological spaces we assemble well known pieces and unfold them into an explicit formula for a strong deformation retraction of the mapping cylinder of f onto its top.

entry.title: Cutting description of trivial 1-cohomology
entry.summary: A characterisation of trivial 1-cohomology for a broad class of metric spaces is presented. The condition ties cohomology and connectedness properties of open sets.

entry.title: Stabilization of the category of simplicial objects in CAT
entry.summary: In this article, we define two equivalent new model structures on $\mathbf{sCat}$ the category of simplicial objects in $\mathbf{Cat}$. Then we construct the corresponding stable model category of spectra $Sp(\mathbf{sCat})$ and make some links with the algebraic $K$-theory via the mapping space.

entry.title: Real Equivariant Bordism for elementary abelian 2-groups
entry.summary: We give a description of real equivariant bordism for elementary abelian 2-groups, which is similar to the description of complex equivariant bordism for the group S^1 x ... x S^1 given by Hanke in 2005.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Homology, Homotopy and Applications, Vol. 15 (2013), No. 1, pp.235-251

entry.title: The Burnside bicategory of groupoids
entry.summary: Several models for the Burnside bicategory of groupoids are described and shown to be equivalent. As observed by the late Gaunce Lewis, the corresponding Burnside category is additive.
entry.arxiv:comment: 21 pp. This draft improves the paper following referee's suggestions

entry.title: Effective chain complexes for twisted products
entry.summary: In the paper weak sufficient conditions for the reduction of the chain complex of a twisted product to a free finitely generated chain complex are found.

entry.title: Bigraded cohomology of Z/2-equivariant Grassmannians
entry.summary: This paper determines the RO(G)-graded Eilenberg-MacLane cohomology of the real, infinite, equivariant Grassmannians in the case G=Z/2. Possible connections with motivic characteristic classes for quadratic bundles are briefly discussed.

entry.title: The cobordism hypothesis
entry.summary: In this expository paper we introduce extended topological quantum field theories and the cobordism hypothesis.
entry.arxiv:comment: 36 pages; v2 has a reference correction

entry.title: Decomposition of loop spaces and periodic problem on $π_*$
entry.summary: We provide a family of spaces localized at 2, whose stable homotopy groups are summands of their unstable homotopy groups. Application to mod 2 Moore spaces are given.

entry.title: Higher order derived functors
entry.summary: We define a notion of higher derived functors, and show how these appear as the E^r term of many commonly used spectral sequences, including the (stable or unstable) Adams spectral sequence.

entry.title: A modular description of ER(2)
entry.summary: We give a description of the maximally unramified extension of completed second Real Johnson-Wilson theory using supersingular elliptic curves with $\Gamma_0(3)$-level structures.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: New York Journal of Mathematics, vol 20 (2014), 743-758

entry.title: On the cohomology of polyhedral products with space pairs $(D^1, S^0)$
entry.summary: In this note we prove that the integer cohomology ring of polyhedral products with space pairs $(D^1, S^0)$ can also be described explicitly by a multiplicative Hochster's formula.

entry.title: Quadratic cohomology
entry.summary: We study homological invariants of smooth families of real quadratic forms as a step towards a "Lagrange multipliers rule in the large" that intends to describe topology of smooth maps in terms of scalar Lagrange functions.

entry.title: Topology of random simplicial complexes: a survey
entry.summary: This expository article is based on a lecture from the Stanford Symposium on Algebraic Topology: Application and New Directions, held in honor of Gunnar Carlsson, Ralph Cohen, and Ib Madsen.

entry.title: Strong cohomological rigidity of toric varieties
entry.summary: Every cohomology ring isomorphism between two non-singular complete toric varieties and quasitoric manifolds, respectively, with second Betti number $2$ is realizable by a diffeomorphism and homeomorphism, respectively.

entry.title: Regular Circle Actions on 2-connected 7-manifolds
entry.summary: We determine the homeomorphism (resp. diffeomorphism) types of those 2-connected 7-manifolds (resp. smooth 2-connected 7-manifolds) that admit regular circle actions (resp. smooth regular circle actions).

entry.title: The Boardman-Vogt tensor product of operadic bimodules
entry.summary: We define and study a lift of the Boardman-Vogt tensor product of operads to bimodules over operads.

entry.title: The Baum-Connes conjecture, Swan group actions and controlled topology
entry.summary: We give a new proof of some cases of the Baum-Connes conjecture along the lines of a proof of the Farrell-Jones conjecture.
entry.arxiv:comment: Phd thesis, 156 pages, main text in english, some formalities in german

entry.title: Almost complex circle actions with few fixed points
entry.summary: We show that almost complex circle actions with exactly three fixed points do not exist in dimension 8 and present an infinite series of 6-dimensional manifolds possessing an almost complex circle action with exactly two fixed points.

entry.title: Transchromatic twisted character maps
entry.summary: Refinements of the transchromatic generalized character maps are constructed by taking into account the torus action on the inertia groupoid (also known as the Fix functor). The relationship between this construction and the geometry of p-divisible groups is made precise.

entry.title: Units in Grothendieck-Witt rings and A^1-spherical fibrations
entry.summary: In this note, we show that the units in Grothendieck-Witt rings extend to an unramified strictly A^1-invariant sheaf of abelian groups on the category of smooth schemes. This implies that there is an A^1-local classifying space of spherical fibrations.

entry.title: J-Groups of Lens Spaces modulo Odd Prime Powers
entry.summary: We describe the J-Groups of lens spaces modulo odd prime powers via relations and rational representations.

entry.title: A case of monoidal uniqueness of algebraic models
entry.summary: We prove that there is at most one algebraic model for modules over the K(1)-local sphere at odd primes that retains some monoidal information.
entry.arxiv:comment: 17 pages, minor changes, to appear in Forum Mathematicum

entry.title: An Operator model for connective K-theory with reality
entry.summary: We construct an explicit model for the connective cover of the spectrum of $K$-theory with reality. This model is a $\ztwo$-equivariant commutative symmetric ring spectrum which identifies with another one due to D. Dugger.

entry.title: An introduction to HKR character theory
entry.summary: The generalized character theory of Hopkins, Kuhn, and Ravenel is an important tool in the study of Morava E-theory and higher height phenomena in chromatic homotopy theory. In this paper, we provide an introduction to HKR character theory with many examples, applications, and alternative points of view.

entry.title: Universal deformation formulas
entry.summary: We give a conceptual explanation of universal deformation formulas for unital associative algebras and prove some results on the structure of their moduli spaces. We then generalize universal deformation formulas to other types of algebras and their diagrams.

entry.title: Mckay Correspondence in Quasitoric Orbifolds
entry.summary: We show Mckay correspondence of Betti numbers of Chen-Ruan coho- mology for omnioriented quasitoric orbifolds. In previous articles with M. Poddar [8], [9], we proved the correspondence for four dimension and six dimensions. Here we deal with the general case.

entry.title: Extending a metric on a simplicial complex
entry.summary: We show how to extend a metric defined on the vertex set of a simplicial complex to the whole simplicial complex, thus correcting a mistake in Mineyev's construction of a flow space.

entry.title: Pathologies in cohomology of non-paracompact Hausdorff spaces
entry.summary: We construct a non-paracompact Hausdorff space for which Cech cohomology does not coincide with sheaf cohomology. Moreover, the sheaf of continuous real-valued functions is neither soft nor acyclic, and our space admits non-numerable principal bundles.

entry.title: Isomorphism Conjecture for Baumslag-Solitar groups
entry.summary: In this paper, we prove the K- and L-theoretical Isomorphism Conjecture for Baumslag-Solitar groups with coefficients in an additive category.

entry.title: The Chern-Gauss-Bonnet Theorem via supersymmetric Euclidean field theories
entry.summary: We prove the Chern-Gauss-Bonnet Theorem using sigma models whose source supermanifolds have super dimension 0|2. Along the way we develop machinery for understanding manifold invariants encoded by families of 0|n-dimensional Euclidean field theories and their quantization.

entry.title: Vector fields on right generalized complex projective Stiefel manifolds
entry.summary: The question of paralleizability and stable parallelizability of a family of manifolds obtained as a quotients of circle action on the complex Stiefel manifolds are studied and settled.
entry.arxiv:comment: To appear in the Proceedings of the Royal Society of Edinburgh

entry.title: The poset of posets
entry.summary: Let X be a finite set. This paper describes some topological and combinatorial properties of the poset \Omega_X of order relations on X. In particular, the homotopy type of all the intervals in \Omega_X is precisely determined, and the M\"obius function of \Omega_X is computed.

entry.title: Nielsen zeta functions on infra-nilmanifolds up to dimension three
entry.summary: In this paper, we will list all possible self-maps on infra-nilmanifolds up to dimension three and we will give the Nielsen zeta function for any of those maps.

entry.title: The modular envelope of the cyclic operad Ass
entry.summary: We give a direct combinatorial proof that the modular envelope of the cyclic operad Ass is the modular operad of (the homeomorphism classes of) 2D compact surfaces with boundary with marked points.

entry.title: Trivial Unit conjecture and Homotopy Theory
entry.summary: A homotopy theoretic description is given for trivial unit conjecture in the group ring ZG.

entry.title: On Levin's generalization of the plus construction
entry.summary: We present a proof of the following theorem of Levin: For every connected CW complex $K$ there is a simply connected CW complex $K^+$ obtained from $K$ by attaching cells of dimension 2 and 3 such that the inclusion $K\to K^+$ induces isomorphisms of homology groups in dimension $>1$.

entry.title: Equivariant bordism of 2-torus manifolds and unitary toric manifolds--a survey
entry.summary: In this paper we survey results and recent progresses on the equivariant bordism classification of 2-torus manifolds and unitary toric manifolds.
entry.arxiv:comment: 15 pages. This survey draws heavily from arXiv:1008.2166

entry.title: Leibniz homology of Lie algebras as functor homology
entry.summary: We prove that Leibniz homology of Lie algebras can be described as functor homology in the category of linear functors from a category associated to the Lie operad.

entry.title: Homology of a Leavitt Path Algebra via Anick's Resolution
entry.summary: The aim of this paper is to calculate the homology of a Leavitt path algebra via Anick's resolution. We show that all homology (in positive degrees) of a Leavitt path algebra is equal to zero.

entry.title: Modeling Collaborations with Persistent Homology
entry.summary: In this paper we describe a model based on persistent homology that describes interactions between mathematicians in terms of collaborations. Some ideas from classical data analysis are used.

entry.title: Long exact sequences for de Rham cohomology of diffeological spaces
entry.summary: In this paper we present the notion of de Rham cohomology with compact support for diffeological spaces. Moreover we shall discuss the existence of three long exact sequences. As a concrete example, we show that long exact sequences exist for the de Rham cohomology of diffeological subcartesian spaces.

entry.title: Morita cohomology and homotopy locally constant sheaves
entry.summary: We identify Morita cohomology, which is a categorification of the cohmology of a topological space X, with the category of homotopy locally constant sheaves of perfect complexes on X.

entry.title: Some examples of non-tidy spaces
entry.summary: We construct a free $\mathbb{Z}_2$-manifold $X_n$ for a positive integer $n$ such that $w_1(X_n)^n \neq 0$, but there is no $\mathbb{Z}_2$-equivariant map from $S^2$ to $X_n$.

entry.title: An A-based cofibrantly generated model category
entry.summary: We develop a cofibrantly generated model category structure in the category of topological spaces in which weak equivalences are A-weak equivalences and such that the generalized CW(A)-complexes are cofibrant objects. With this structure the exponential law turns out to be a Quillen adjunction.

entry.title: On the periodic $v_2$-self-map of $A_1$
entry.summary: We prove that the minimal $v_2$ self-map of the 2-local spectrum $A_1$ is 32 periodic.

entry.title: Lecture notes on torsions
entry.summary: These are the lecture notes for the introductory course on Whitehead, Reidemeister and Ray-Singer torsions, given by the author at the University of Zurich in Spring semester 2014.

entry.title: Comparison of models for $(\infty, n)$-categories, II
entry.summary: In this paper we complete a chain of explicit Quillen equivalences between the model category for $\Theta_{n+1}$-spaces and the model category of small categories enriched in $\Theta_n$-spaces.

entry.title: Kan subdivision and products of simplicial sets
entry.summary: The canonical map from the Kan subdivision of a product of finite simplicial sets to the product of the Kan subdivisions is a simple map, in the sense that its geometric realization has contractible point inverses.

entry.title: Fibrancy of Partial Model Categories
entry.summary: We investigate fibrancy conditions in the Thomason model structure on the category of small categories. In particular, we show that the category of weak equivalences of a partial model category is fibrant. Furthermore, we describe connections to calculi of fractions.

entry.title: Topology of random geometric complexes: a survey
entry.summary: In this expository article, we survey the rapidly emerging area of random geometric simplicial complexes.

entry.title: Some Remarks on Realization of Simplicial Algebras in Cat
entry.summary: In this paper we discuss why the passage from simplicial algebras over a Cat operad to algebras over that operad involves apparently unavoidable technicalities.

entry.title: Chromatic fracture cubes
entry.summary: In this note, we construct a general form of the chromatic fracture cube, using a convenient characterization of the total homotopy fiber, and deduce a decomposition of the E(n)-local stable homotopy category.

entry.title: Two Models for the Homotopy Theory of Cocomplete Homotopy Theories
entry.summary: We prove that the homotopy theory of cofibration categories is equivalent to the homotopy theory of cocomplete quasicategories. This is achieved by presenting both homotopy theories as fibration categories and constructing an explicit equivalence between them.

entry.title: Moduli spaces of 6 and 7-dimensional complete intersections
entry.summary: This paper proves the existence of homeomorphic (diffeomorphic) complex 6-dimensional (7-dim) complete intersections that belong to components of the moduli space of different dimensions. These results are given as a supplement to earlier result on 5-dimensional complete intersections.

entry.title: Chromatic completion
entry.summary: We study the limit of the chromatic tower for not necessarily finite spectra, obtaining a generalization of the chromatic convergence theorem of Hopkins and Ravenel. Moreover, we prove that in general this limit does not coincide with harmonic localization, thereby answering a question of Ravenel's.

entry.title: Morava k(s)^* -rings of the extensions of C_p by the products of good groups under diagonal action
entry.summary: This note provides a theorem on good groups in the sense of Hopkins-Kuhn-Ravenel and some relevant examples.

entry.title: Homology groups of spaces of non-resultant quadratic polynomial systems in R^3
entry.summary: We calculate rational homology groups of spaces of non-resultant (i.e. having no non-trivial common zeros) systems of homogemeous quadratic polynomials in R^3

entry.title: A delooping of the space of string links
entry.summary: We exhibit an explicit delooping of the space of string links with $m$ components in the hypercube $I^{n}$, for $n\geq 4$ and $m\geq 1$.

entry.title: Failure of flat descent of model structures on module categories
entry.summary: We prove that the collection of model structures on (quasicoherent) module categories does not obey flat descent. In particular, it fails to be a separated presheaf, in the fppf topology, on Artin stacks.

entry.title: The Hochschild homology of A(1)
entry.summary: We compute the Hochschild homology of $A(1)$, the subalgebra of the $2$-primary Steenrod algebra generated by the first two Steenrod squares, $\Sq^1,\Sq^2$. The computation is accomplished using several May-type spectral sequences.

entry.title: The motivic Adams vanishing line of slope 1/2
entry.summary: We establish a motivic version of Adams' vanishing line of slope 1/2 in the cohomology of the motivic Steenrod algebra over the complex numbers.

entry.title: Perturbative N=2 supersymmetric quantum mechanics and L-theory with complex coefficients
entry.summary: We construct L-theory with complex coefficients from the geometry of 1|2-dimensional perturbative mechanics. Methods of perturbative quantization lead to wrong-way maps that we identify with those coming from the MSO-orientation of L-theory tensored with the complex numbers.

entry.title: Rational homology of the order complex of zero sets of homogeneous quadratic polynomial systems in $R^3$
entry.summary: The naturally topologized order complex of proper algebraic subsets in $RP^2$, defined by systems of quadratic forms, has rational homology of $S^{13}$
entry.arxiv:comment: 20 pages, 3 figures. arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1412.8194

entry.title: Topological T-duality is twisted Atiyah duality
entry.summary: We show that the topological T-duality for circle bundles introduced in work of Bouwknegt-Evslin-Mathai can be interpreted as a form of Atiyah duality for twisted K-theory.

entry.title: Categorification of the colored $\mathfrak{sl}_3$-invariant
entry.summary: We give explicit resolutions of all finite dimensional, simple $U_q(\mathfrak{sl_3})$-modules. We use these resolutions to categorify the colored $\mathfrak{sl}_3$-invariant of framed links via a complex of complexes of graded $\mathbb{Z}$-modules.

entry.title: On some problems related to the Hilbert-Smith conjecture
entry.summary: We present a reduction of the Hilbert-Smith conjecture in the case of the finite dimensional orbit space to some algebraic topology problems.

entry.title: A short treatise on Equivariant Gamma spaces
entry.summary: Equivariant $\Gamma$-spaces model equivariant infinite loop spaces. In this article, we show that there exists a connective Quillen equivalence between the category of equivariant $\Gamma$-spaces and the category of orthogonal spectra.
entry.arxiv:comment: There were mistakes in the previous version and they have been removed

entry.title: On RO(G)-graded equivariant "ordinary" cohomology where G is a power of Z/2
entry.summary: We compute the complete RO(G)-graded coefficients of "ordinary" cohomology with coefficients in Z/2 for G=(Z/2)^n.

entry.title: Chern numbers of manifolds with torus action
entry.summary: We show that every set of numbers that occurs as the set of Chern numbers of an almost complex manifold $M^{2n}$, $n\geqslant 3$, may be realized as the set of Chern numbers of a connected almost complex manifold with an almost complex action of two-dimensional compact torus.

entry.title: Chow ring and BP-theory of the extraspecial 2-group of order 32
entry.summary: We write down the mod 2 Chow ring of the classifying space of the central product of two dihedral groups of order 8. This Chow ring has nilpotent elements.

entry.title: Quasicategories of Frames of Cofibration Categories
entry.summary: We show that the quasicategory of frames of a cofibration category, introduced by the second-named author, is equivalent to its simplicial localization.

entry.title: Topological complexity of spatial polygon spaces
entry.summary: Using known results about their integral cohomology ring, we prove that the topological complexity of the space of n-gons in R^3 with prescribed side lengths equals 2n-5, assuming that the space is nonempty and does not contain any straight-line polygons.

entry.title: Fundamental Group Algorithm for low dimensional tessellated CW complexes
entry.summary: We present a detailed description of a fundamental group algorithm based on Forman's combinatorial version of Morse theory. We use this algorithm in a classification problem of prime knots up to 14 crossings.

entry.title: Functorial CW-approximation
entry.summary: The usual construction of a CW-approximation is functorial up to homotopy, but it is not functorial. In this note, we construct a functorial CW-approximation. Our construction takes inclusions of subspaces into inclusions of subcomplexes, and commutes with intersections of subspaces of a fixed space.

entry.title: Modular equations for Lubin-Tate formal groups at chromatic level 2
entry.summary: We give an integral lift of the Kronecker congruence for moduli of finite subgroups of elliptic curves. This leads to a uniform presentation for the power operation structure on Morava E-theories of height 2.

entry.title: A Construction on Operads Applicable to Homology Operations and the Minimal Model
entry.summary: We define a construction on operads which yields a new description of the minimal model. The construction also allows us to define algebraic structures on the homology of chain complexes with homologously trivial operad algebra structures, thus exposing nontrivial structure where none is apparent.

entry.title: Deciding almost freeness of an action is NP-hard
entry.summary: We encode a compact Lie group action on a compact manifold by the Sullivan model of its Borel construction. We then prove that deciding whether this action is almost free is NP-hard.

entry.title: Cohn localization of finite group rings
entry.summary: The purpose of this paper is to give a complete description of the Cohn localization of the augmentation map $Z[G]\rightarrow Z$ when $G$ is any finite group.

entry.title: Model $\infty$-categories II: Quillen adjunctions
entry.summary: We prove that various structures on model $\infty$-categories descend to corresponding structures on their localizations: (i) Quillen adjunctions; (ii) two-variable Quillen adjunctions; (iii) monoidal and symmetric monoidal model structures; and (iv) enriched model structures.

entry.title: Twisted equivariant differential K-theory from gauged supersymmetric mechanics
entry.summary: We use the geometry of the space of fields for gauged supersymmetric mechanics to construct the twisted differential equivariant K-theory of a manifold with an action by a finite group.

entry.title: The Friedlander-Milnor conjectures
entry.summary: We prove the Milnor and the Friedlander-Milnor conjectures.

entry.title: On the structure of open equivariant topological conformal field theories
entry.summary: We give a classification of open equivariant topological conformal field theories in terms of Calabi-Yau $A_\infty$-categories endowed with a group action.
entry.arxiv:comment: arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1503.02465

entry.title: Circle actions with two fixed points
entry.summary: We prove that if the circle group acts smooth and unitary on 2n-dimensional stably complex manifold with two isolated fixed points and it is not bound equivariantly, then n=1 or 3. Our proof relies on the rigid Hirzebruch genera.

entry.title: (Co)homology of Spectral Categories
entry.summary: In this article we develop the cotangent complex and (co)homology theories for spectral categories. Along the way, we reproduce standard model structures on spectral categories. As applications, we show that the invariants to descend to stable $\infty$-categories and we prove a stabilization result for spectral categories.

entry.title: Hochschild homology and cohomology for involutive $A_\infty$-algebras
entry.summary: We present a study of the homological algebra of bimodules over $A_\infty$-algebras endowed with an involution. Furthermore we introduce a derived description of Hochschild homology and cohomology for involutive $A_\infty$-algebras.

entry.title: Module sectional category of products
entry.summary: Extending a result of F\'elix-Halperin-Lemaire on Lusternik-Schnirelmann category of products, we prove additivity of a rational approximation for Schwarz's sectional category with respect to products of fibrations.

entry.title: Betti numbers of unordered configuration spaces of the torus
entry.summary: Using a method of F\'elix and Thomas we compute the Betti numbers of unordered configuration spaces of the torus.
entry.arxiv:comment: 7 pages; extended to the unstable range

entry.title: Homological stability for configuration spaces of orbifolds
entry.summary: We prove that homological stability holds for configuration spaces of orbifolds. This builds on the work of Bailes' thesis where he proves that the stabilisation maps are injective.
entry.arxiv:comment: 11 pages, comments welcome. An appendix was added

entry.title: Cellular approximations of fusion systems
entry.summary: In this paper we study the cellularization of classifying spaces of saturated fusion systems with respect to classifying spaces of finite $p$-groups. We give explicit criteria to decide when a classifying space is cellular and we give explicit computations for a family of exotic examples.

entry.title: Cellularity of hermitian K-theory and Witt theory
entry.summary: Hermitian K-theory and Witt-theory are cellular in the sense of stable motivic homotopy theory over any base scheme without points of characteristic two.

entry.title: Z/2-equivariant and R-motivic stable stems
entry.summary: We establish an isomorphism between the stable homotopy groups of the 2-completed motivic sphere spectrum over the real numbers and the corresponding stable homotopy groups of the 2-completed Z/2-equivariant sphere spectrum, in a certain range of dimensions.

entry.title: On Quillen's conjecture for p-solvable groups
entry.summary: We give a new proof of Quillen's conjecture for solvable groups via a geometric and explicit method. For p-solvable groups, we provide both a new proof using the Classification of Finite Simple Groups and an asymptotic version without employing it.

entry.title: On the cohomology classes of planar polygon spaces
entry.summary: We obtain an explicit formula for the Poincare duality isomorphism H^{n-3}(Mbar(ell)) to Z/2 for the space of isometry classes of n-gons with specified side lengths, if ell is monogenic in the sense of Hausmann-Rodriguez. This has potential application to topological complexity.

entry.title: Burnside Condition on Some Intersection Subgroups
entry.summary: In this paper, using the notions graphs, core graphs, immersions and covering maps of graphs, introduced by Stallings in 1983, we prove the Burnside condition for the intersection of subgroups of free groups with Burnside condition.

entry.title: Segal objects and the Grothendieck construction
entry.summary: We discuss right fibrations in the $\infty$-categorical context of Segal objects in a category V and prove some basic results about these.

entry.title: $p$-local stable cohomological rigidity of quasitoric manifolds
entry.summary: It is proved that if two quasitoric manifolds of dimension $\le 2p^2-4$ for a prime $p$ have isomorphic cohomology rings, then they have the same $p$-local stable homotopy type.

entry.title: Mod 3 Chern classes and generators
entry.summary: We show the non-triviality of the mod 3 Chern class of degree 324 of the adjoint representation of the exceptional Lie group E_8.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: Proc. Japan Acad. Ser. A Math. Sci. 93 (2017), no. 7, 55--60

entry.title: Paths of the directed suspension
entry.summary: We prove that the loop space of the directed suspension of a directed space is homotopy equivalent to the James construction. In particular, it does not depend on the directed structure of a given directed space.

entry.title: Periodic points on T - fiber bundles over the circle
entry.summary: The main purppose this work is to study periodic points of fiber-preserving maps on fiber bundles with base circle and fiber torus.

entry.title: Higher associativity of Moore spectra
entry.summary: The Moore spectrum $M_p(i)$ is the cofiber of the $p^{i}$ map on the sphere spectrum. For a fixed $p$ and $n$, we find a lower bound on $i$ for which a unital $A_n$-structure on $M_p(i)$ is guaranteed. This bound is dependent on the stable homotopy groups of spheres.

entry.title: Topological embeddings of disks via configuration categories
entry.summary: The functor that takes a manifold to its configuration category exhibits a type of full faithfulness in some cases.

entry.title: Dimension rigidity of lattices in semisimple Lie groups
entry.summary: We prove that if $\Gamma$ is a lattice in the group of isometries of a symmetric space of non-compact type without euclidean factors, then the virtual cohomological dimension of $\Gamma$ equals its proper geometric dimension.

entry.title: On Spaces of Topological Complexity Two
entry.summary: In this paper we consider the classification of minimal cellular structures of spaces of topological complexity two under some hypotheses on there graded cohomological algebra. This continues the method used by M.Grant et al. in [1].

entry.title: Symmetric products and subgroup lattices
entry.summary: Let G be a finite group. In this paper we show that the rational homotopy groups of symmetric products of the G-equivariant sphere spectrum are naturally isomorphic to the rational homology groups of certain subcomplexes of the subgroup lattice of G.

entry.title: Topological complexity of collision-free multi-tasking motion planning on orientable surfaces
entry.summary: We compute the higher topological complexity of ordered configuration spaces of orientable surfaces, thus extending Cohen-Farber's description of the ordinary topological complexity of those spaces.

entry.title: Spherical posets from commuting elements
entry.summary: In this paper we study the poset of cosets of abelian subgroups in an extraspecial p-group. We prove that the universal cover of the nerve of this poset is homotopy equivalent to a wedge of n-spheres where 2n is the rank of its Frattini quotient.

entry.title: Hurewicz fibrations in elementary toposes
entry.summary: We introduce Hurewicz fibrations and related topological notions based on elementary axiomatisations of cohesion and interval in a topos. This is enough to have a model of basic homotopy type theory. In particular, realisability toposes over partial combinatory algebras are amenable to this technique.

entry.title: Morse-Bott inequalities for manifolds with boundary
entry.summary: In the present paper, we define Morse-Bott functions on manifolds with boundary which are generalizations of Morse functions and show Morse-Bott inequalities for these manifolds.

entry.title: Manifolds with the fixed point property and their squares
entry.summary: The Cartesian squares (powers) of manifolds with the fixed point property (f.p.p.) are considered. Examples of manifolds with the f.p.p. are constructed whose symmetric squares fail to have the f.p.p..

entry.title: Endomorphisms of Exotic Models
entry.summary: We calculate the endomorphism dga of Franke's exotic algebraic model for the $K$-local stable homotopy category at odd primes. We unravel its original abstract structure to give explicit generators, differentials and products.

entry.title: How Dennis realized he had `invented' $L_\infty$-algebras a.k.a. strongly homotopy Lie algebras
entry.summary: This is my attempt to rediscover how Dennis realized that he had discovered/invented $L_\infty$-algebras a.k.a. strongly homotopy Lie algebras before my colleagues and I defined them.

entry.title: A user's guide: Completed power operations for Morava $E$-theory
entry.summary: The user's guide provides a behind-the-scenes look at the paper of that title.
entry.arxiv:comment: More information on the User's Guides project is available at mathusersguides.com

entry.title: The equivariant Chern character as super holonomy on loop stacks
entry.summary: We study super parallel transport around super loops in a quotient stack, and show that this geometry constructs a global version of the equivariant Chern character.

entry.title: Semistable Graph Homology
entry.summary: Using the orbicell decomposition of the Deligne-Mumford compactification of the moduli space of Riemann surfaces studied previously, a chain complex based on semistable ribbon graphs is constructed which is an extension of Konsevich's graph homology.
entry.arxiv:comment: 21 pages, 16 figures. arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:0708.2441

entry.title: On the covering type of a space
entry.summary: We introduce the notion of the "covering type" of a space, which is more subtle that the notion of Lusternik Schnirelman category. It measures the complexity of a space which arises from coverings by contractible subspaces whose non-empty intersections are also contractible.

entry.title: Cayley Transform on Stiefel manifolds
entry.summary: We define a Cayley transform on Stiefel manifolds. Applications to the Lusternik-Schnirelmann category and optimisation problems are presented.

entry.title: Examples of descent up to nilpotence
entry.summary: We give a survey of the ideas of descent and nilpotence. We focus on examples arising from chromatic homotopy theory and from group actions, as well as a few examples in algebra.

entry.title: The Rational Sectional Category of Certain Universal Fibrations
entry.summary: We prove that the sectional category of the universal fibration with fibre X, for X any space that satisfies a well-known conjecture of Halperin, equals one after rationalization.

entry.title: Moore's Conjecture for Polyhedral Products
entry.summary: Moore's Conjecture is shown to hold for generalized moment-angle complexes and a criterion is proved that determines when a polyhedral product is elliptic or hyperbolic.

entry.title: Spectral sequences via examples
entry.summary: These are lecture notes for a short course about spectral sequences that was held at M\'alaga, October 18--20 (2016), during the "Fifth Young Spanish Topologists Meeting". The approach was to illustrate the basic notions via fully computed examples arising from Algebraic Topology and Group Theory.

entry.title: Measure theory and classifying spaces
entry.summary: We construct classifying spaces for discrete and compact Lie groups, with the property that they are topological groups and complete metric spaces in a natural way. We sketch a program in view of extending these constructions.

entry.title: Dijkgraaf-Witten $Z_2$-invariants for Seifert manifolds
entry.summary: In this short paper we compute the values of Dijkgraaf-Witten invariants over $Z_2$ for all orientable Seifert manifolds with orientable bases.

entry.title: The projective model structure on contractions
entry.summary: We prove that the projective model structure on the category of unbounded cochain complexes extends naturally to the category of contractions. The proof is completely elementary and we do not assume familiarity with model categories.

entry.title: Rational models for automorphisms of fiber bundles
entry.summary: Given a fiber bundle, we construct a differential graded Lie algebra model for the classifying space of the monoid of homotopy equivalences of the base covered by a fiberwise isomorphism of the total space.

entry.title: A few examples of $R-$good and $R-$bad classifying spaces
entry.summary: For a commutative ring $R$, in contrast to the completion in the sense of Bousfield and Kan at just a prime integer, there cannot exist spaces which are good and bad in an arbitrary way.

entry.title: Labeled homology of higher-dimensional automata
entry.summary: We define labeling homomorphisms on the cubical homology of higher-dimensional automata and show that they are natural with respect to cubical dimaps and compatible with tensor products. We also indicate two possible applications of labeled homology in concurrency theory.

entry.title: Recursive formulas for the motivic Milnor basis
entry.summary: We give recursive formulas for the generating elements in the Milnor basis of the mod 2 motivic Steenrod algebra.
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: New York Journal of Mathematics 23 (2017) 49-58, http://nyjm.albany.edu/j/2017/23-4.html

entry.title: A Distance Between Filtered Spaces Via Tripods
entry.summary: We present a simplified treatment of stability of filtrations on finite spaces. Interestingly, we can lift the stability result for combinatorial filtrations from [CSEM06] to the case when two filtrations live on different spaces without directly invoking the concept of interleaving.

entry.title: Vanishing in stable motivic homotopy sheaves
entry.summary: We determine systematic regions in which the bigraded homotopy sheaves of the motivic sphere spectrum vanish.

entry.title: Cubical and cosimplicial descent
entry.summary: We prove that algebraic K-theory, topological Hochschild homology and topological cyclic homology satisfy cubical and cosimplicial descent at connective structured ring spectra along 1-connected maps of such ring spectra.

entry.title: Quasitoric totally normally split representatives in unitary cobordism ring
entry.summary: The present paper generalises the results of Ray and Buchstaber-Ray, Buchstaber-Panov-Ray in unitary cobordism theory. I prove that any class $x\in \Omega^{*}_{U}$ of the unitary cobordism ring contains a quasitoric totally normally and tangentially split manifold.

entry.title: On Mimura's extension problem
entry.summary: We determine the group strucure of the $23$-rd homotopy group $\pi_{23}(G_2 : 2)$, where $G_2$ is the Lie group of exceptional type, which hasn't been determined for $50$ years.

entry.title: Models for classifying spaces for $\mathbb{Z}\rtimes \mathbb{Z}$
entry.summary: We construct two models for the classifying space for the family of infinite cyclic subgroups of the fundamental group of the Klein bottle. These examples do not fit in general constructions previously done, for example, for hyperbolic groups.

entry.title: The cobordism hypothesis
entry.summary: Assuming a conjecture about factorization homology with adjoints, we prove the cobordism hypothesis, after Baez-Dolan, Costello, Hopkins-Lurie, and Lurie.
entry.arxiv:comment: 36 pages, slightly revised; preliminary version, comments welcome

entry.title: Anderson and Gorenstein duality
entry.summary: The paper relates the Gorenstein duality statements studied by the first author to the Anderson duality statements studied by the second author, and explains how to use local cohomology and invariant theory to understand the numerology of shifts in simple cases.

entry.title: On the realization problem for $N_\infty$ operads
entry.summary: We show that every indexing system arises as the admissible sets of a large, but explicit, categorical $N_\infty$ operad. This positively resolves a conjecture of Blumberg and Hill on the classification of $N_\infty$ operads.

entry.title: On Conjugates and Adjoint Descent
entry.summary: In this note we present an $\infty$-categorical framework for descent along adjunctions and a general formula for counting conjugates up to equivalence which unifies several known formulae from different fields.

entry.title: A moment-angle manifold whose cohomology is not torsion free
entry.summary: In this paper we give a method to construct moment-angle manifolds whose cohomologies are not torsion free. We also give method to describe the corresponding simplicial sphere by its non-faces.

entry.title: Moduli of $Π$-algebras
entry.summary: We describe a homotopy-theoretic approach to the moduli of $\Pi$-algebras of Blanc-Dwyer-Goerss using the $\infty$-category $P_{\Sigma}(Sph)$ of product-preserving presheaves on finite-wedges of positive-dimensional spheres, reproving all of their results in this new setting.

entry.title: $A_\infty$ structures and Massey products
entry.summary: We study the relationship between the higher Massey products on the cohomology $H$ of a differential graded algebra, and the $A_\infty$ structures induced on $H$ via homotopy transfer techniques.

entry.title: Cycle index sum for non-k-equal configurations
entry.summary: We compute the cycle index sum of the symmetric group action on the homology of the configuration spaces of points in a Euclidean space with the condition that no $k$ of them are equal.

entry.title: Free Finite Group Actions on Rational Homology 3--Spheres
entry.summary: We use methods from the cohomology of groups to describe the finite groups which can act freely and homologically trivially on closed 3-manifolds which are rational homology spheres.

entry.title: Bialgebraic proof of the existence of cup-product in the cohomology of racks and quandles
entry.summary: We retrieve the graded commutative algebra structure of rack and quandle cohomology by purely algebraic means.

entry.title: A $C_2$-equivariant analog of Mahowald's Thom spectrum theorem
entry.summary: We prove that the $C_2$-equivariant Eilenberg-MacLane spectrum associated to the constant Mackey functor $\underline{\mathbb{F}}_2$ is equivalent to a Thom spectrum over ${\Omega^\rho S^{\rho + 1}}$.

entry.title: Cellular covers of local groups
entry.summary: We prove that, in the category of groups, the composition of a cellularization and a localization functor need not be idempotent. This provides a negative answer to a question of Emmanuel Dror Farjoun.

entry.title: Verification of the Quillen conjecture for $SL_2(\mathbb Z[\sqrt{-2}][1/2])$
entry.summary: We compute the mod 2 cohomology of $SL_2(\mathbb Z[\sqrt{-2}][1/2])$ via the amalgamated decomposition of the latter group. The result confirms the Quillen conjecture for $SL_2(\mathbb Z[\sqrt{-2}][1/2])$ .

entry.title: Homotopy Theoretic Classification of Symmetry Protected Phases
entry.summary: We classify a number of symmetry protected phases using Freed-Hopkins' homotopy theoretic classification. Along the way we compute the low-dimensional homotopy groups of a number of novel cobordism spectra.

entry.title: Notes on the bounded cohomology theory
entry.summary: The paper is devoted to a generalized and improved version of author's approach to Gromov bounded cohomology theory. In particular, the awkward countability assumption is removed and the aspects related to homological algebra are clarified. The exposition is largely self-contained.

entry.title: Rational homotopy theory via Sullivan models: a survey
entry.summary: This survey contains the main results in rational homotopy, from the beginning to the most recent ones. It makes the status of the art, gives a short presentation of some areas where rational homotopy has been used, and contains a lot of important open problems

entry.title: A canonical basis of two-cycles on a K3 surface
entry.summary: We construct a canonical basis of two-cycles, on a $K3$ surface, in which the intersection form takes the canonical form $2E_8(-1) \oplus 3H$. The basic elements are realized by formal sums of smooth submanifolds.

entry.title: An elementary proof for Poincare Duality with local coefficients
entry.summary: An proof of Poincare Duality with local coefficients and with compact support is provided. The proof does not require Sheaf Theory or anything equivalent and is thus more accessible for the general audience.

entry.title: Contractible configuration spaces
entry.summary: Let $F(X,k)$ be the configuration spaces of ordered $k-$tuples of distinct points in the space $X$. Using the Fadell and Neuwirth's fibration, we prove that the configuration space $F(M,k)$ of certain topological manifolds $M$, is not contractible.

entry.title: A lower bound for higher topological complexity of real projective space
entry.summary: We obtain an explicit formula for the best lower bound for the higher topological complexity, TC_k(P^n), of real projective space implied by mod 2 cohomology.

entry.title: Torsions of integral homology and cohomology of real Grassmannians
entry.summary: According to a result of Ehresmann, the torsions of integral homology of real Grassmannian are all of order $2$. In this note, We compute the $\mathbb{Z}_2$-dimensions of torsions in the integral homology and cohomology of real Grassmannian.

entry.title: Collision-free motion planning on manifolds with boundary
entry.summary: This paper concerns the study of the homotopy type of the ordered configuration space for manifolds with boundary and as an application we will study the collision free motion planning problem on manifolds with boundary.

entry.title: On the geometric fixed points of real topological Hochschild homology
entry.summary: We compute the component group of the derived $G$-geometric fixed points of the real topological Hochschild homology of a ring with anti-involution, where $G$ denotes the Galois group Gal($\mathbb{C}$/$\mathbb{R}$) of order 2.

entry.title: Classification of equivariant real vector bundles over a circle
entry.summary: This is a continuation of the authors' previous work [math.AT/9910001] on classification of equivariant complex vector bundles over a circle. In this paper we classify equivariant real vector bundles over a circle with a compact Lie group action, by characterizing the fiber representations of them, and by using the result of the complex case. We also treat the triviality of them. The basic phenomenon is similar to the complex case but more complicated here.

entry.title: Algebraic Poincare cobordism
entry.summary: This paper is an introduction to the use of the cobordism of chain complexes with Poincar\'e duality in surgery theory. It is a companion to the author's paper "An introduction to algebraic surgery" math.AT/0008071 (to appear in Volume 2 of Surveys in Surgery Theory, Ann. of Maths. Studies, Princeton, 2001) which is an introduction to algebraic surgery using forms and formations.
entry.arxiv:comment: AMSTEX 43 pages, conm-p.sty, ams-p.sty, ams-spec.sty and xypic input to appear in Proc. 1999 Stanford conference in honour of 60th birthday of R.J.Milgram

entry.title: Hypersurface complements, Milnor fibers and minimality of arrangements
entry.summary: We describe a new relation between the topology of hypersurface complements, Milnor fibers and degree of gradient mappings. The main tools are polar curves and the affine Lefschetz theory developped by H. Hamm and A. N\'emethi. In the special case of the hyperplane arrangements, we strengthen some results due to Orlik and Terao (see Math. Ann. 301(1995)) and obtain an independant proof for the minimality of hyperplane arrangements (see Randell math.AT/0011101 for another proof of this result).

entry.title: Concurrent Process up to Homotopy (I)
entry.summary: Globular CW-complexes and flows are both geometric models of concurrent processes which allow to model in a precise way the notion of dihomotopy. Dihomotopy is an equivalence relation which preserves computer-scientific properties like the presence or not of deadlock. One constructs an embedding from globular CW-complexes to flows and one proves that two globular CW-complexes are dihomotopic if and only if the corresponding flows are dihomotopic. This note is the first one presenting some of the results of math.AT/0201252.
entry.arxiv:comment: English abstract ; French text ; projet de note aux C.R.A.S
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris Ser. I Math., 336(7):593-596, 2003

entry.title: Concurrent Process up to Homotopy (II)
entry.summary: One proves that the category of globular CW-complexes up to dihomotopy is equivalent to the category of flows up to weak dihomotopy. This theorem generalizes the classical theorem which states that the category of CW-complexes up to homotopy is equivalent to the category of topological spaces up to weak homotopy. This note is the second one presenting some of the results of math.AT/0201252.
entry.arxiv:comment: English abstract ; French text ; projet de note aux C.R.A.S
entry.arxiv:journal_ref: C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris Ser. I Math., 336(8):647-650, 2003

entry.title: A model category for the homotopy theory of concurrency
entry.summary: We construct a cofibrantly generated model structure on the category of flows such that any flow is fibrant and such that two cofibrant flows are homotopy equivalent for this model structure if and only if they are S-homotopy equivalent. This result provides an interpretation of the notion of S-homotopy equivalence in the framework of model categories.
entry.arxiv:comment: 45 pages ; 4 figure ; First paper corresponding to the content of math.AT/0201252 ; final version

entry.title: Secondary derived functors and the Adams spectral sequence
entry.summary: Classical homological algebra takes place in additive categories. In homotopy theory such additive categories arise as homotopy categories of ``additive groupoid enriched categories'', in which a secondary analog of homological algebra can be performed. We introduce secondary chain complexes and secondary resolutions leading to the concept of secondary derived functors. As a main result we show that the E_3-term of the Adams spectral sequence can be expressed as a secondary derived functor. This result can be used to compute the E_3-term explicitly by an algorithm.

entry.title: Exact cohomology sequences with integral coefficients for torus actions
entry.summary: Using methods applied by Atiyah in equivariant K-theory, Bredon obtained exact sequences for the relative cohomologies (with rational coefficients) of the equivariant skeletons of (sufficiently nice) T-spaces, T=(S^1)^n, with free equivariant cohomology over the cohomology of BT. Here we characterise those finite T-CW complexes with connected isotropy groups for which an analogous result holds with integral coefficients.
entry.arxiv:comment: similar main result as in our preprint math.AT/0307112, but the proof is more elementary; 10 pages; final version

entry.title: Integrating L-infinity algebras
entry.summary: Given an n-term L-infinity algebra L, we construct a Kan simplicial manifold which we think of as the 'Lie n-group' integrating L. This extends work of Getzler math.AT/0404003 . In the case of an ordinary Lie algebra, our construction gives the simplicial classifying space of the corresponding simply connect Lie group. In the case of the string Lie 2-algebra of Baez and Crans, this recovers the model of the string group introduced in math.QA/0504123 .

entry.title: K-theory of torus manifolds
entry.summary: The {\it torus manifolds} have been defined and studied by M. Masuda and T. Panov (arXiv:math.AT/0306100) who in particular describe its cohomology ring structure. In this note we shall describe the topological $K$-ring of a class of torus manifolds (those for which the orbit space under the action of the compact torus is a {\it homology polytope} whose {\it nerve} is a {shellable} simplicial complex) in terms of generators and relations. Since these torus manifolds include the class of quasi-toric manifolds this is a generalisation of earlier results due to the author and P. Sankaran (arXiv: math.AG/0504107).

entry.title: Rings of definition of smooth and proper dg-algebras
entry.summary: This is a companion paper to math.AT/0609762. For a filtered colimit of commutative rings k=colim k_i, we prove that the homotopy theory of smooth and proper dg-algebras over k is the colimit of the homotopy theories of smooth and proper dg-algebras over k_i. As a consequence, we deduce that any smooth and proper dg-algebra can be defined over a commutative Z-algebra of finite type.

entry.title: Gröbner bases and some immersion theorems for Grassmann manifolds G_{3,n}
entry.summary: A Gr\"obner basis for the ideal determining mod 2 cohomology of Grassmannian G_{3,n} is obtained. This is used, along with the method of obstruction theory, to establish some new immersion results for these manifolds.
entry.arxiv:comment: This is a preprint from 2011. It is already cited in arXiv:1305.0420 [math.AT] as well as in some other already published papers, so we have decided to make it available

entry.title: A combinatorial formula for the Pontrjagin classes
entry.summary: A combinatorial formula for the Pontrjagin classes of a triangulated manifold is given. The main ingredients are oriented matroid theory and a modified formulation of Chern-Weil theory.

entry.title: The rigid analytic period mapping, Lubin-Tate space, and stable homotopy theory
entry.summary: The geometry of the Lubin-Tate space of deformations of a formal group is studied via an \'etale, rigid analytic map from the deformation space to projective space. This leads to a simple description of the equivariant canonical bundle of the deformation space which, in turn, yields a formula for the dualizing complex in stable homotopy theory.

entry.title: Not all free arrangements are $K(π,1)$
entry.summary: We produce a one-parameter family of hyperplane arrangements that are counterexamples to the conjecture of Saito that the complexified complement of a free arrangement is $K(\pi,1)$. These arrangements are the restriction of a one-parameter family of arrangements that arose in the study of tilings of certain centrally symmetric octagons. This other family is discussed as well.

entry.title: Some new embeddings and nonimmersions of real projective spaces
entry.summary: We use obstruction theory to prove that if alpha(n)=2, then RP^{16n+8} cannot be immersed in R^{32n+3} and RP^{16n+10} cannot be immersed in R^{32n+11}, and that if alpha(n)>2, then RP^{8n+4} can be embedded in R^{16n+1}. These are new results.
entry.arxiv:comment: 12 pages. Submitted to Boardman Conference Proceedings. See also http://www.lehigh.edu/~dmd1/pubs.html

entry.title: Spaces of polynomials with roots of bounded multiplicity
entry.summary: We describe an alternative approach to some results of Vassiliev on spaces of polynomials, by using the scanning method which was used by Segal in his investigation of spaces of rational functions. We explain how these two approaches are related by the Smale-Hirsch Principle or the h-Principle of Gromov. We obtain several generalizations, which may be of interest in their own right.

entry.title: Leibniz Cohomology and the Calculus of Variations
entry.summary: In this paper we continue the investigation of Loday's Leibniz cohomology as a new invariant for differentiable manifolds. In particular the Leibniz coboundary of a k-tensor (in the sense of differential geometry) is computed in a local coordinate chart and then interpreted in terms of the calculus of variations. For example, the Leibniz coboundary of the metric two-tensor reduces to the first variation of arc length.

entry.title: Spaces of Rational Loops on a Real Projective Space
entry.summary: We show that the loop spaces of real projective spaces are topologically approximated by the spaces of rational maps from RP(1) to RP(n). As a byproduct of our constructions we obtain an interpretation of the Kronecker characteristic (degree) of an ornament via particle spaces.

entry.title: On the relation between lifting obstructions and ordinary obstructions
entry.summary: We consider partial liftings of maps at fibrations and compare the primary obstruction to extend the lifting with the obstruction to extend the lifting as a simple map into the total space. A relation between these two obstructions is proved for the case when the fiber is an Eilenberg-MacLane space. Furthermore it is shown that this result specialises to well known facts about secondary obstructions.
entry.arxiv:comment: LaTeX, 9 pages. To appear in Top. Appl

entry.title: The Homotopy Type of hyperbolic Monopole Orbit Spaces
entry.summary: We prove that the space of gauge equivalence classes of U(1)-invariant connections on some SU(2)-principle bundles over the 4-sphere S^4 is weakly homotopy equivalent to a component of the second loop space of the 2-sphere S^2.
entry.arxiv:comment: 8 pages, AMS-Tex, to appear in Proceedings of the AMS

entry.title: The algebraic construction of the Novikov complex of a circle-valued Morse function
entry.summary: The Novikov complex of a circle-valued Morse function is constructed algebraically from the Morse-Smale complex of the restriction to a fundamental domain of the real-valued Morse function on the pullback infinite cyclic cover.
entry.arxiv:comment: 49 pages, amstex, with pictex and xypic diagrams. Revision of 1999 version, to appear in Mathematische Annalen

entry.title: Iterated Peiffer pairings in the Moore complex of a simplicial group
entry.summary: We introduce a pairing structure within the Moore complex NG of a simplicial group G and use it to investigate generators for NG_n\cap D_n where D_n is the subgroup generated by degenerate elements. This is applied to the study of algebraic models for homotopy types.

entry.title: On formulas of the Lannes and Viro-Polyak type for the finite degree invariants
entry.summary: Vassiliev's knot invariants can be computed in different ways but many of them as Kontsevich integral are very difficult. We consider more visual diagram formulas of the type Polyak-Viro and give new diagram formula for the two basic Vassiliev invariant of degree 4

entry.title: Explicit formulas for the Vassiliev knot invariants
entry.summary: Vassiliev's knot invariants can be computed in different ways but many of them as Kontsevich integral are very difficult. We consider more visual diagram formulas of the type Polyak-Viro and give new diagram formula for the two basic Vassiliev invariant of degree 4.
entry.arxiv:comment: The brief version of this paper is in materials of International Conference "Monodromie et \'equations diff\'erentielles en th\'eorie des singularit\'es et des repr\'esentations de groupes."

entry.title: Diagram formulas of the Viro-Polyak type for finit degree invariants
entry.summary: Vassiliev's knot invariants can be computed in different ways but many of them as Kontsevich integral are very difficult. We consider more visual diagram formulas of the type Polyak-Viro and give new diagram formula for the two basic Vassiliev invariant of degree 4.

entry.title: Homotopy Algebras are Homotopy Algebras
entry.summary: We prove that strongly homotopy algebras (such as $A_\infty$, $C_\infty$, sh Lie, $B_\infty$, $G_\infty$,...) are homotopically invariant in the category of chain complexes. An important consequence is a rigorous proof that `strongly homotopy structures transfer over chain homotopy equivalences.'
entry.arxiv:comment: LaTeX 2.09, 31 pages, article 12pt + bezier, substantially revised

entry.title: Vanishing lines in generalized Adams spectral sequences are generic
entry.summary: We show that in a generalized Adams spectral sequence, the presence of a vanishing line of fixed slope (at some term of the spectral sequence, with some intercept) is a generic property.
entry.arxiv:comment: 11 pages. Published copy, also available at http://www.maths.warwick.ac.uk/gt/GTVol3/paper7.abs.html

entry.title: Homology manifold bordism
entry.summary: The Bryant-Ferry-Mio-Weinberger surgery exact sequence for high-dimensional compact ANR homology manifolds is used to obtain transversality, splitting and bordism results for homology manifolds, generalizing previous work of Johnston.
entry.arxiv:comment: 45 pages, 8 EPS figures, to appear in Trans. A.M.S

entry.title: Transversality Obstructions and Equivariant Bordism for G=Z/2
entry.summary: In this paper we compute homotopical equivariant bordism for the group ${\bf Z/2}$, namely $MO^{\bf Z/2}$, geometric equivariant bordism $\Omega^{\bf Z/2}_*$, and their quotient as modules over geometric bordism. This quotient is a module of stable transversality obstructions. In doing these computations, we use the techniques the author developed in the complex setting. Because we are working in the real setting only with Z/2, these techniques simplify greatly.

entry.title: Representations of the homotopy surface category of a simply connected space
entry.summary: We introduce the homotopy surface category of a space which generalizes the 1+1-dimensional cobordism category of circles and surfaces to the situation where one introduces a background space. We explain how for a simply connected background space, monoidal functors from this category to vector spaces can be interpreted in terms of Frobenius algebras with additional structure.

entry.title: A classification of S^3-bundles over S^4
entry.summary: The paper is withdrawn due to some errors.

entry.title: Equivariant Elliptic Cohomology and Rigidity
entry.summary: Equivariant elliptic cohomology with complex coefficients was defined axiomatically by Ginzburg, Kapranov and Vasserot and constructed by Grojnowski. We give an invariant definition of S^1-equivariant elliptic cohomology, and use it to give an entirely cohomological proof of the rigidity theorem of Witten for the elliptic genus. We also state and prove a rigidity theorem for families of elliptic genera.

entry.title: Algebraic structure of the loop space Bockstein spectral sequence
entry.summary: Let X be a finite, n-dimensional, r-connected CW complex. We prove the following theorem: If p \geq n/r is an odd prime, then the loop space homology Bockstein spectral sequence modulo p is a spectral sequence of universal enveloping algebras over differential graded Lie algebras.

entry.title: Realizing coalgebras over the Steenrod algebra
entry.summary: We describe algebraic obstruction theories for realizing an abstract coalgebra K_* over the mod p Steenrod algebra as the homology of a topological space, and for distinguishing between the p-homotopy types of different realizations. The theories are expressed in terms of the Quillen cohomology of K_*.

entry.title: CW simplicial resolutions of spaces, with an application to loop spaces
entry.summary: We show how a certain type of CW simplicial resolutions of space by wedges of spheres may be constructed for any topological space, and how such resolutions yield an obstruction theory for a given space X to be a loop space.

entry.title: A braided simplicial group
entry.summary: By studying braid group actions on Milnor's construction of the 1-sphere, we show that the general higher homotopy group of the 3-sphere is the fixed set of the pure braid group action on certain combinatorially described group. We also give certain representation of higher differentials in the Adams spectral sequence for the homotopy groups of the 2-sphere.

entry.title: Interchanging homotopy limits and colimits in CAT
entry.summary: Let $I$,$J$ be small categories and $C:I\times J@>>>\CAT$ a functor to the category of small categories. We show that if $I$ has a final object then the canonical map $\operatorname{hocolim}_J\operatorname{holim}_IC@>>>\operatorname{holim}_I \operatorname{hocolim}_JC$ is a strong homotopy equivalence.

entry.title: Ideal Perturbation Lemma
entry.summary: We explain the essence of perturbation problems. The key to understanding is the structure of chain homotopy equivalence -- the standard one must be replaced by a finer notion which we call a strong chain homotopy equivalence. We prove an Ideal Perturbation Lemma and show how both new and classical results follow from this ideal statement.
entry.arxiv:comment: Introduction substantially revised and some typos corrected

entry.title: Every homotopy theory of simplicial algebras admits a proper model
entry.summary: We show that any closed model category of simplicial algebras over an algebraic theory is Quillen equivalent to a proper closed model category. By ``simplicial algebra'' we mean any category of algebras over a simplicial algebraic theory, which is allowed to be multi-sorted. The results have applications to the construction of localization model category structures.

entry.title: Dickson Invariants in the image of the Steenrod Square
entry.summary: Let D_n be the Dickson invariant ring of F_2[X_1,...,X_n] acted by the general linear group GL(n,\F_2). In this paper, we provide an elementary proof of the conjecture by [Hung]: each element in D_n is in the image of the Steenrod square in F_2[X_1,...,X_n], where n>3.

entry.title: Minimal Models for Non-Free Circle Actions
entry.summary: Let $\Phi \colon \sbat \times M \to M$ be a smooth action of the unit circle $ \sbat$ on a manifold $M$. In this work, we compute the minimal model of $M$ in terms of the orbit space $B$ and the fixed point set $F\subset B$, as a dg-module over the Sullivan's minimal model of $B$.

entry.title: A classification of $S^3$-bundles over $S^4$
entry.summary: We classify the total spaces of bundles over the four sphere with fiber a three sphere up to orientation preserving and reversing homotopy equivalence, homeomorphism and diffeomorphism. These total spaces have been of interest to both topologists and geometers. It has recently been shown by Grove and Ziller that each of these total spaces admits metrics with nonnegative sectional curvature.

entry.title: Absolute non-Archimedean polyhedral expansions of ultrauniform spaces
entry.summary: This work is devoted to the investigation of the problem about inverse mapping systems expansions of ultrauniform spaces $X$ using polyhedra over non-Archimedean locally compact fields $\bf L$. Theorems about expansions of complete ultrametric and ultrauniform spaces are proved. Absolute polyhedral expansions and inverse mapping systems of expansions for non-complete spaces are investigated. This article also contains results about a relation of $dim (X)$ and dimensions of polyhedra over $\bf L$.

entry.title: Topology of billiard problems, II
entry.summary: We give topological lower bounds on the number of periodic and closed trajectories in strictly convex smooth billiards. We use variational reduction admitting a finite group of symmetries and apply topological approach based on equivariant Morse and Lusternik - Schnirelman theories. The paper continues results published in math.DG/9911226 and math.DG/0006049

entry.title: Combinatorial model categories have presentations
entry.summary: We show that every combinatorial model category can be obtained, up to Quillen equivalence, by localizing a model category of diagrams of simplicial sets. This says that any combinatorial model category can be built up from a category of `generators' and a set of `relations'---that is, any combinatorial model category has a presentation.
